text:
#존로크통치론 #공진성 #쌤앤파커스
p.7~8 : 전직 대통령의 구속과 이른바 ‘미투(#metoo)’ 운동에 의한 리더들의 몰락에는 하나의 공통된 원인이 있다. 그것은 자신들이 가진 권력의 한계를 그들이 스스로 인식하지 못했다는 것이다. 권력자들은 자신들이 가진 권력이 그 한계 안에서 사용될 때에만 정당할 수 있다는 것을 알지 못했거나 알면서도 무시했다. ‘권력의 한계’는 먼저 권력 자체의 성격에 의해, 다음으로는 그 권력의 대상이 되는 사람들의 동의에 의해 결정된다. 그러므로 권력의 대상이 되는 사람들이 스스로 권력의 성격을 어떻게 이해하느냐가 사실상 권력의 한계를 결정한다고 말할 수 있다. 우리가 오늘날 경험하고 있는 변화는 권력의 성격에 대한 사람들의 생각이 바뀌는 현상이다. 달리 말하면, 권력의 성격을 과거와 다르게 이해하는 사람의 수가 늘어나고 있는 것이다.

#서문 마음에 든다.
오랜만에 고전이라 쉽게 읽히진 않지만
대학때나 공부한 존 로크라니.
새로운 기분😝

text:
the worst thing for me isn´t the fact that it seems like nobody seems to care or understand.
the worst thing is, that the people i tell my story, are not even willing to understand. “you are talking normal, so you can´t be ill.”
“you are smiling, so you are not depressed. “
“you haven´t tried to kill yourself, can´t be that bad.”
“just try to think positive, you are the problem. “
“try to wear brighter clothes, you will feel better. “
“you are always so strong, you can´t have a mental illness.” i am dealing with depression, anxiety, burnout and who knows what else, for over 10 years now. but for all this years i never talked to a specialist for mental health. i only spoke to my normal doctor and got some medicine (antidepressant).
i can recommend to everyone, that thinks „maybe i am more, than just sad.“: go to a specialised doctor and ask him or her what they think.
when i took the step and first spoke to a specialist, i was really happy to talk to someone that knows what i am going though.
don’t be afraid to talk about your problems, your sadness or loneliness and your feelings! there will always be someone that can and will understand you!
***
#staystrong #metoo

text: today was also rough, as i made the decision to unfollow someone i've looked up to for 16 years. i've got nothing but love in my heart for the dude, but it's hard to see someone you care about going against what you know to be right and just. for the record: if you have a friend who is accused of sexual assault, i can absolutely understand you wanting to stand with them and question those allegations. i can understand comforting and supporting them privately. what i cannot understand is using a public platform with hudreds of thousands of followers, many of whom you know are victims of the same abuse your friend is accused of committing, many of whom have confessed their deepest, most vulnerable moments to you, to continue to promote the person under those allegations. what i absolutely refuse to condone is turning off comments specifically on certain posts to avoid any discussion on the topic from people you've very clearly hurt, people who have in the past been your strongest supporters. it all leaves a bad taste in my mouth and was all done without tact.

text:
finally, the last part of my #rebelstory with which i hoped to answer some of your questions and hopefully inspire some of you to walk the way you’ve chosen, even if it often means to walk alone. ——————————————
today my story  continues here in western europe. the place where dreams have more chances to become reality, the place where human dignity is respected, the place where equality is advocated. however, paradoxically, also the place where all the achievements, rights are often taken for granted. the illusion that the rights people have here wont be ever taken away, the democratic process wont ever move backwards, lead many to give up, to stop carrying about their rights, to stop participating in public debates and leave all the responsibility on a small group of politicians. women sometimes chose to keep silence as they are told their status is improving and their single experiences should not be shared in public. but silence is a death penalty for our personalities and our dreams. many want us silent to prevent us from making a change. i know it well, as in 2015 not far from here, in copenhagen, i was giving a talk on freedom of speech. i couldn't express my ideas because of kalashnikov shots fired by a person moved by dogmas at the moment i was speaking on the stage. for him it was easier to take a gun and kill people than to hear a different opinion, then to accept that we have right to express our aspirations and demands. from that terrorist attack, that as other experiences had affected me for life, i’ve also learned. my shaking voice became now louder and more confident. i’ve learned the necessity to speak out. i said to myself we all have to be louder that their kalashnikovs. we all have to break the silence that the old rotten system expects from us. 
i tell my story simply to remind that hope can rise from despair, light from darkness, strength from weakness, courage from fear… today, we all see how victims speak out with #metoo movement, how they manifest their strength after horrifying experiences, how they sound loud after years of silence. that’s the story... the moral is: never let anyone bully you into silence. #femen

text:
++feminismus pt3++
.
notwendige grundlage des kapitalistischen systems bildet die reproduktionsarbeit, wofür die frau durch die herrschenden rollenzuschreibungen vorgesehen ist. insbesondere die unbezahlte reproduktive arbeit ist tägliche voraussetzung der produktionsarbeit. jene besteht unter anderem aus der erledigung des haushaltes, aber auch aus der versorgung der kinder und anderen familienmitgliedern. jegliche arbeit außerhalb des arbeitsplatzes soll, in einer bürgerlichen familie, dem mann durch die frau abgenommen werden. dies soll es dem mann ermöglichen, sich bestmöglich von der arbeit als lohnabhängiger zu erholen. die unterdrückung der frau ist somit notwendig um den kapitalismus aufrecht zu erhalten. auch sex zählt in diesem familienbild zur erhohlung des mannes und wird deshalb oft in einer ehe verlangt. .
dadurch, dass die frau als kompensation für die arbeit dient, kann alltäglicher sexismus und sexualisierte gewalt entstehen. diese äußern sich in der objektifizierung des frauenkörpers und handlungen wie hinterher pfeifen und angrapschen.
.
diese systematische unterdrückung und ausbeutung der frau wird aber auch unterstützt und getragen von sexueller gewalt. .
die person, die in einer familie ökonomisch überlegen ist, ist auch automatisch in der machtposition, da andere von ihr abhängig sind. dass die abhängigen meistens frauen sind, ist in unseren gesetzen fest verankert, z.b. durch kritisch zu betrachtende abtreibungsgesetze, wenig unterstützung im falle eines kindes, ungleicher bezahlung und zu wenig ganztägiger kitaplätze. auch durch fragwürdige steuergesetze aus der ns-zeit für ehepaare wird die frau in die position der ökonomisch abhängigen gedrückt. dass der staat kaum interesse daran hat, frauen eine gerechtere position zu verschaffen und unser sozialsystem zu verbessern, ist eindeutig zu erkennen.
.
fortsetzung folgt. .
#feminismus#sexismus#kapitalismus#metoo#161crew#antifa#altona

text:
nå, det har rusat fram - det senaste året med #metoo och knytblus till valdag, vardag och fest. höjda röster, stillsamma mumlande toner - och många knappt hörbara. de värst drabbade sitter månne fortfarande på sina kammare? och skäms? ja inte osannolikt är det så. lägg sedan till mediala och samhälleliga tecken på ännu en polariserad debatt i den långa raden. jag (av)skyr dem allt mer.

och annars då?

jag och du och han och hon och hen.
ditt, mitt - dutt, datt.
plus en jävla massa gammalt dalt och darr.
det som hände, det som inte hände; det som gick som det gick ... och förresten, vad var det egentligen som hände!

oavsett ‘då’ lever nu: följderna, ovissheten, skammen, skulden, vanmakten och viljan till förändring. allt som kanske inte alltid är som det ser ut att vara berättar sammanfattande: - sannerligen, var dag har nog av sitt.

ja himmelska helvete med en nyans av paradiset på jorden - tack för #endagitaget .

avslutningsvis ett boktips (på repris) från #storytel . en titel som väl faller rätt i tiden? ingen stilistisk pärla, kan tyckas, men en innehållsligt viktig skildring som kan ändra kurs för den som krälar på botten.

maria blomqvists liv med bokens ”erik” är ingalunda unikt. toner kan förstås variera i grad av subtilitet, men härskare härskar och det onormala blir lätt normalt om den giftiga grodden har bördig grund. vargar och får, omlott i en allt glättigare och mer tillrättalagd,  låtsad verklighet.

och för saks skull, visst kan hen som härskar  heta ”erika”, men statistiken talar tydligt - nästan lika tydligt som de tysta kvinnornas dolda andetag ... i mina känslor är de ohörbara ropen skrik som skär.

no more fucks to give? korrekt. #nmftg . låt oss se varandra, i ärlighet, för att ha en chans att hjälpas åt i livet. 💜
#withalittlehelp

text:
uncage her from all the social norms and let her drive the car onto her desired paths.  you feel she is not capable of wandering alone just give her one chance! the modern girl is wild enough to drive a bike to any corner of this world. she carries a wild light which nobody can ever blow! the modern woman is savage & is a perfect amalgamation of soft & simple! she is born with such stardust light which can illuminate all the darkness of the world. and that’s why she seeks no permission and no approvals. 
let her be herself, dare not to tame her!

text:
07102018 part 7
...so my ex spends time with his mom 24/7. he tells me not to go downstairs. he uses her bathroom & walks around in his underwear in front of her. they act like a real couple at home. eating side by side, going out, shopping together, walking sofia for hours, even when its late in the evening so she comes home with big mosquito bites that gets infected. he also spends time in the room with his mom with the lights out; tiptoeng out of the room. its been really disgusting. i've never seen anything like it. they dont invite me at all and when they come home they give sofia to me as if im just a caretaker. the neighbors are asking me why im always excluded. when i voice out my concerns my ex tells me its a "patriarchal house and i pay for everything so you have no say at all". ...so many things has happened in the past especially in the past 3 months. im glad that we are out of that mad house. since we left, sofia has been giggling more & shes sleeping soundly. i apologize if there is no positivity in my posts. this is about the ugly truth of a bad marriage. #domesticviolence is never pretty. when its done, all you have left are the scars & memories that will hopefully go away one day. they say time heals everything and sofia & i are waiting until it hurts no more. i know i've been through a lot but sofia has been through more because i can defend myself, speak up, & fight back. but she cant. she needs time to heal from all that carelessness & neglect. my ex tells me that if we divorce sofia will not grow up normally. i say if we dont divorce then she really wont. i know children who were raised by only their mothers who grew up well. its all about how i do it. and i know i can do it right with guidance from above. i know i can. for all you women out there dont be a victim! you are worth all the love in the world. dont be afraid to speak up & walk away. in fact, please do everything to get away! you can do it on your own. remember: god counts a woman's tears. know youre important! this society as you know it wouldnt exist without you! speak up for the truth! social media must advocate more for the truth than for pretty little things. sofia is safe!❤

text:
there is a ‘durga’ in every girl .
many people do not know how to treat a woman or behave around them yet they will happily go in a temple and worship goddess 'durga'. this navratri i hope people take a moment to appreciate the durga within every single woman around them and not just the deity in the temple.  we all need to learn how to respect and treat the women in our lives. be it our sisters, mothers, colleagues or simply a girl walking down the street, perhaps then there will be no need for a #metoo movement ever again!  i am sure that would make ma durga very happy. happy navratri everyone.

text: "kenties #metoo-kampanjan myötä erityisesti naisiin liitettyjä ahtaita ulkonäkömuotteja ja muita stereotypioita on alettu näkyvästi rikkomaan, mikä on hienoa! toistaiseksi tämä näkyvyyttä saava rajojen rikkominen tuntuu kuitenkin olevan melko suppeaa: valkoisia, hoikkia, able-bodied naisia. missä ovat esimerkiksi lihavat, rodullistetut, transsukupuoliset tai liikuntarajoitteiset naiset? jotenkin haluaisin ajatella, että intersektionaalisen feminismin myötä olisimme jo siinä pisteessä, ettemme keskittyisi ihan näin suppeaan otokseen naiseudesta, vaan pyrkisimme tuomaan esille muitakin tasa-arvoasioita kuin vain kahden sukupuolen välinen tasa-arvo." linkki biossa 💭✏️

text_retweet:
#repost @feministerna
・・・
metoo måste prioriteras 
för över tio år sedan grundade tarana burke metoo för att nå kvinnor i underprivilegierade områden som blivit utsatta för mäns våld. en kampanj som fick ny luft under vingarna när skådespelerskan alyssa milano twittrade #metoo och uppmanade andra kvinnor att dela med sig av sina upplevelser av sexuella trakasserier och övergrepp. idag har ett år sedan milanos tweet och hundratusentals kvinnor världen över har gått med i rörelsen, inte minst här i sverige där den vuxit sig starkare än någon annanstans. 
feministiskt initiativ är ett parti sprunget ur kvinnorörelsen och har alltid arbetat för att bekämpa mäns våld mot kvinnor. därför välkomnar vi de förslag på åtgärder som kommit från samordningen för metoo-uppropen och ger de vårt helhjärtade stöd. vi anser att det är av yttersta vikt att förslagen förverkligas och vi kommer fortsätta driva politik och påverkan för att nå det mål vi alltid har arbetat för – en värld fri från våld. 
vi vill inte att det ska ta ytterligare tio år innan något händer. det är viktigare än någonsin att vi fortsätter lyssna på de vittnesmål som finns i metoo, tar tillvara på den kompetens uppropen besitter och att politiker tar sitt ansvar och påbörjar verklig förändring. metoo måste prioriteras. feministiskt initiativ kommer därför dedikera november månad till att särskilt fokusera på just de frågor metoo handlar om. på vilket sätt får du snart se. viktigast är som vanligt att vi gör det tillsammans.

text:
in de wake of the #metoo movement we are reading about all kinds of violations and experiences that women from all professional fields are and have suffered from... in a country thats on  the threshold of empowering women to not just speak up but also take action against the predator .. even if shez alone.. is reason enough to celebrate ... but is this enough ? will it sustain? maybe it will curb de intentions of a few creeps who may think twice before doing this or find ways to continue wid a full proof plan.

we r into betibachao... lets now work on betekosikhao... teach your young sons on how to treat a woman... that no means no..
that no woman is weak or superior.. but equal

she can be ur partner she can be ur competitor she can be ur saviour but not ur slave.

that lets get a doormat who lets u walk all over her but does not speak is good to have as home decor but not as a blessing  that u need who will challenge u to b a better version of yourself.. lets teach our lil boys that hitting a woman is not ok... pushing her around is not... over powering her is not.

that when they grow up... with power comes responsibility... and de biggest challenge is knowing how to use it... lets focus on educating boys.

the beautiful thing about learning is no one can ever take it away from you.

when we educate the minds of 0ur little boys lets also educate their hearts💖💖💖💖💖💖💖💖💖💖💖💖

text:
navigating relationships in the time of ‘performance anxiety’.
.
framing debates for ourselves in a time when we are still processing the what, why, and how of the absurd narratives, personalities, and the traits we missed, is not an easy task. the conversations are affecting a lot more than we notice, and nobody is able to navigate them. unlearning where we have come from and remapping relationships is a step-by-step process, nuanced in individual situations, and depending on patience to support it.
.
sharing links to some articles/books/people, i have come across in the past few months, some are more applicable to my life directly than not, but it opens up the nuances of the debate. if you have any other forms of writing, films, debates and more, that have allowed you to explore this uncharted territory with a little help, let me know.
.

- the metoo movement parsing the generational divide.
- the metoo movement navigating sex in the grey zone
2. longreads:
- the great stink
aeon:
- how do we understand sexual pleasure in the age of consent
3. the guardian:
- revisiting matilda in an age of women’s rage
4. new yorker:
- cat person
- angels in america - jessica jones season 2 is a portrait of female rage
- nanette - the comedian forcing stand up to confront the #metoo era
- reading ovid in the age of #metoo
- jian ghomeshi john hockenberry and the lows of patriarchal physics 
5. scroll:
- anita nairs eating wasps (yet to read this entirely)

7. the paris review:
- what do we do with the art of monstrous men
8. chup - dr deepa narayan (yet to read this, although if you ever get to meet her and engage in her perspectives, do it)
- medium: reading chup

- how forgiveness has been weaponized against women

text:
a little girl awoke 
at midnight,
with clenched fists,
sweaty forehead, 
and a heavy heart.

she looked around
but found nothing,
just the monster
created by her thoughts.

sadly,
it wasn't just a delusion.
she could feel
a hand 
crawling
from her waist 
under her little skirt.

it was her uncle
who asked her 
for a kiss
and to keep it a secret, 
he would give her
her favourite chocolates.

before this day
she did know
how to deal with 
the monster that hid
under her bed
but
she didn't know
how to deal 
with the monster
on her bed. 
#childabuse ~ soniya kapoor / @secretsouldesires #secretsoulfesires .

text: «το γεγονός πως παντρεύτηκα στην ηλικία των 22 τον τομ κρουζ, είναι κάτι που πάντα με βρίσκει απρόθυμη να θίξω, επειδή τώρα είμαι παντρεμένη με τον άνθρωπο που είναι η μεγάλη αγάπη μου [κιθ ούρμπαν], και το αισθάνομαι ως ασέβεια. τούτου λεχθέντος, παντρεύτηκα πολύ νέα, και σίγουρα δεν ήταν δύναμη για μένα - ήταν προστασία. παντρεύτηκα από έρωτα, αλλά ο γάμος μου με έναν εξαιρετικά ισχυρό άντρα κρατούσε μακριά τις σεξουαλικές παρενοχλήσεις. εργαζόμουν, αλλά ήμουν σε ένα κουκούλι. έτσι, όταν βγήκα από αυτό στα 32, 33 μου, ήταν σαν να έπρεπε να μεγαλώσω». το 2017 η κίντμαν και το τηλεοπτικό «big little lies», στο οποίο ήταν παραγωγός και πρωταγωνίστρια, συνάντησαν το σωστό timing λίγο πριν ξεσπάσει το κίνημα #metoo. στο the cut η κίντμαν συμπληρώνει πως: «φυσικά και είχα #metoo στιγμές - από τότε που ήμουν μικρή! αλλά θέλω να τις εκθέσω σε ένα άρθρο; όχι. βγαίνουν στη δουλειά μου; απολύτως. είμαι ανοιχτή, ωμή. θέλω να διοχετεύσω την εμπειρία και το συναίσθημά μου, να τα χρησιμοποιήσω - και δεν μιλώ μόνο για τη σεξουαλική παρενόχληση. μιλώ για την απώλεια, το θάνατο, την πλήρη εμπειρία της ζωής. αλλά πρέπει να γίνεται από τους σωστούς ανθρώπους, για να μην γίνει καταχρηστικό».

text_retweet:
reposting from last year: 
he was the leader for our freshman orientation group at the college i attended. everyone loved him. all the girls flirted with him. every person on campus stopped to say hi or ask how he was doing. he was attentive, answering all the questions, getting even the shyest in the group (me) to participate. he had a pretty amazing story of overcoming a tragedy in his life. he was a bodybuilder, his buddies bragging about him being mr. arkansas. he was fun and exciting and popular. and he had eyes only for me. i was so overwhelmed by him. and out of all the girls on campus, i couldn’t believe he was paying attention to me. he fooled me...and everyone around us. so, when things took a turn later on....i believed him when he said nobody would listen to me. he was  perfect. i was the problem. nobody would believe me. so let me say this: i believe you. if you need someone to stand up with you, i’m your girl. even if it’s messy or unexpected or painful, i will believe you. if the world says he’s perfect but you say he’s not, i’ll believe you. if he has dozens and dozens of friends who love him but you say that’s not the real him, i’ll believe you. if he fools everyone around him but you know the truth, i’ll believe you. #domesticviolenceawareness #stopdomesticviolence #realmendonthit #loveshouldnthurt #metoo

text:
(part 2)

further, mr ganapathy notes that the accusations are made against the “high and mighty”. it may be that accusations against the famous are the ones that get primetime media coverage. the hindu reported on october 16, 2018 that scores of women raised the issue of being molested during the open street festival held on october 13, 2018 in mysore. in light of their statements on social media platforms, the karnataka state women’s commission has taken suo moto cognizance of the matter and has begun investigations. there was no one high or mighty involved in this case. mr ganapathy seems to suggest that men cannot be blamed for their instinctive behaviour since “after food, animals seek sex”. this is particularly ironic since the incident occurred during a food festival.

revealing that his ignorance extends from biology to the law, mr ganapathy also points to a mythological legal provision that requires women to register protest at the time of a sexual assault, in the absence of which she is deemed to have given consent. given that mr ganapathy refers to hamlet’s queen gertrude and her discomfort in being reminded of her haste to remarry after the death of her husband, one wonders whether mr ganapathy has some discomfort of his own with regard to the issue of sexual abuse that he is so eager to decry a movement of survivors of abuse trying to air their grievances. i would urge the editor-in-chief to not use the star of mysore as a platform to air his witlessness. me thinks mr ganapathy protests the protests too much!

#starofmysore
#metooindia
#metoo #metoomovement

text:
nu är det ett år sedan som mitt och många andras flöden i sociala medier fylldes med #metoo till en följd av att skådespelerskan alyssa milano den 15 oktober 2017 twittrade raderna: ”if you’ve been sexually harassed or assaulted write ‘me too’ as a reply to this tweet.”
✊🏽
ett av mina främsta budord som sexolog och en som arbetar med sexuella övergrepp, är att vi måste få ett språk för att beskriva våra erfarenheter för att kunna bearbeta vad som hänt. ett språk är en av de största gåvorna #metoo gav oss, samt tydligheten för den som inte insett tidigare att destruktiva och könsbundna normer genomsyrar alla samhällsskikt. något måste göras. ✊🏾
och det gäller att börja i tid. barn och sexuellt laddade beteenden tycker många är läskigt, men vi måste ta vårt vuxenansvar. prata med barn om kroppslig och mental integritet, verbalisering av känslor och samtycke så kommer vi undvika ett nytt #metoo om något decennium. #sexologi #korsstygnsaktivism

text:
almost exactly a year ago the #metoomovement went viral on social media. an outpour of stories about firsthand experiences of sexual violence was shared by people from all corners of the world. 🌏
.
this movement marked a shift in conversation. over the past 4 years, we’ve offered both awareness and prevention programs on sexual violence. up until october 2017, ruam chuay’s team was primarily asked to help raise awareness.
.
now, the question we get from our community changed from “is this really a problem?” to “what can we do about it?”
.
we’ve delivered our signature interpersonal violence prevention program to over 150 students. not only exploring the issue but sharing ways we can each play a part in preventing this type of violence in our communities.
.
if you would like to shift the conversation in your community, we’re here to help. send us a message to bring a prevention program to your school or workplace.
.
#metoomovement #metoo #breakthesilence #conversationsforchange #sparkingconversation #creatingchange #sexualviolenceprevention #awareness #dvawarenessmonth #interpersonalviolence #socialchange

it seems to me that some guys (men?!) have problems following the rules of social conduct when they want to interact with girls and women, so allow me to give you a few groundrules to follow:
.
👉🏽 making uninvited sexual passes is not okay - not even on instagram
👉🏽 commenting on a woman’s body is not okay - not even on instagram
👉🏽 having a fetish is your business, so don’t push it on to someone who isn’t willingly a part of it. always make sure you have the other person’s consent - even on instagram(!!)
👉🏽 shaming another person’s body is f*****g not okay - not even on instagram
👉🏽 if you dont’t have anything nice to say, please be quiet - even on instagram 🤷🏼‍♀️
.

text_retweet:
#repost @thecriticspoetry (@get_repost)
・・・
#metoo 
the original poem was from the book ' i am a woman, and i am an indian.'
_____

me too is a viral hashtag that was/is spread against assault and harassment on women. the scale with which women from around the globe participated, and now in india clearly suggested how many have faced the blunt terror of this masculine world. if this is the state of women from creamy layer and of the upper class that knows social media and hashtag, then imagine the situation of women from deprived and suburban background.

read the poem below
_______

misogyny in society –
in form of discrimination,
in form of violence and abuse
in form of androcentrism
can we escape?
___

misogyny in society _
in form of patriarchy
in form of tradition and myths
in form of religions and customs
can we escape?
___

it is time we stomp our foot firm.
it is time we made our noise loud.
let the monsters be shed off their veils.
let not the victims be victimized.
raise and rise for the future that is to come.
___

#metoo #thecriticspoetry
#poetry #iamawomanandiamanindian
#women #womenempowerment #genderequality #poetrycommunity #poetryoftheday #poems #poem #writings #writersofindia #metooindia

text:
cw: se*ual ab*se
i am about to completely let my guard down for... whoever may see this. this isn’t for views. this isn’t so i can be “trendy” or “cool”. my hair is wild, i’m in my underwear, and i just finished crying. today i came to the realization that i have serious ptsd. some bad memories from when i was a child have come up. and i spent tonight crying, shaking, rocking back and forth trying to just process it all. as an adult we are taught to just let the past go. to pretend that what happened cannot and doesn’t have to impact you later on. that’s bullshit. our pasts heavily dictate who we are obviously so why wouldn’t we worry about it? reflect and grow. that’s what i’m trying. i came to the realization though that i had a (not so close) family member sexually abuse me when i was younger. i just know it happened. idk if anyone will believe me because it’s been so many years. and people may fucking... idk assume that because i couldn’t remember it until now that it’s fake. this isn’t fake. this feeling i had cannot be faked. my entire childhood has been stripped down and taken away from me. i have no childhood anymore. i never talk about my feelings really. and i am taking this time to show you this side of me because i want anyone who is dealing with this kind of shit to know you are not alone. you truly aren’t. everyone’s experiences with trauma may be different. but that doesn’t mean you have to cope alone. don’t do that to yourself, seriously. don’t take on this trauma alone. it’s okay to develop a support group to fall on when you’re struggling. and if you don’t have one. well fuck, now you do. i’m your dad now. message me. call me. whatever you need to do. i’ll be there. and if you don’t have my contact information dm me and you will. when i say i love each and every one of my children (you) i mean it. you’re loved. and while whatever you’re going through may be hard. if you stay you’ll get through it. bb. you gotta keep that chin up and keep moving forward anyway you can. stay safe. stay hydrated. love you. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
#cannabiscommunity #abuse #metoo #gettingstronger #help #lgbt #trauma #ptsd #survivor

ok, please let's talk about this. i think there is a lot of fear and trepidation that has come from the current #metooindia movement. some of it rightly so. however i do not believe this is the end of romance and relationships! i think we need to have an honest and frank conversation about what is and isn't appropriate. this post is not a tirade. i urge you to post your comments asking the questions you may have about what is acceptable behavior and at what stage it could be deemed assault. men please ask. women please share. we must begin the conversation somewhere. you will not be judged for asking questions. questions are good, questions are important. i urge everyone not to turn this into an argument here. let's try to help each other understand... ♂️♀️

text: att torskarna ”köper en tjänst” är bullshit. ”vad kostar du?” frågar dom. inte ”vad kostar det”. för dom är du = det. du är en sak, en grej, ett objekt. redan i kontakten via mess eller kik visar dom att dom inte ser mig som en människa. dom hyr ens kropp, lite som att hyra en bil och vill att man ska berätta om den, visa bilder på den (testköra), säga vad den klarar av och sen prutas det om vad ”den” är värd. den är lika med du. jag hör ofta från olika tyckare att ”kunden köper en tjänst inte en kropp” och det verkar va hämtat ur källa röven eftersom ca alla torskar jag skriver eller har skrivit med frågar ”vad kostar du” inte ”det”. lura sig själv bäst som vill men i torskens ögon är man ett ”det”, ett objekt och det är därför jag aldrig kommer ge mig angående att sexköp är övergrepp, det är patriarkal maktutövning och det är inte något frigörande eller stärkande i att bli köpt. så jag har en beef med t.ex rfsl som tar parti för sexköpsliberaler och istället för att se sexköp som övergrepp tipsar om hur man ”säljer sex på ett säkert sätt”. jag har en beef med alla som pratar om val och kastar maktanalysen åt sidan. jag har en beef med alla som tror att det är feminism och sexuell frigörelse att va en handelsvara. ”vad kostar du”. ”har du bilder på fittan”. torsken är den med makt, torsken betalar inte för en tjänst utan för att hyra en människa och bestämma över henne. därför ser jag inte relevansen att prata om valfrihet hit och dit när det oavsett i alla lägen är patriarkal maktutövning och den som blir köpt avhumaniseras och reduceras till ett objekt. intersektionell feminism handlar inte om att tillåta patriarkal maktutövning eller annan maktutövning från män eller folk med mer cash. och självklart kan man vara feminist och sälja sex, men det är inte feminism att sälja sex. #prostitution #utanskyddsnät #metoo #intedinhora #feminism

text:
наша традиционная рубрика #цифрадня сегодня обращает внимание на, так называемые, неочевидные виды насилия.
⠀
проявление свободной воли и решение человека на получение образования, освоение той или иной профессии либо работы в выбранной для себя области - является свободным выбором и не может подвергаться унижениям, обструкции или запрету. 
насилие по отношению к партнерше/партнеру часто маскируется под чрезмерную опеку, сопровождаемую словами "не надо тебе работать, лучше расти наших детей", "куда тебе учиться, загляни в свой паспорт", "что ты все этой чушью занимаешься, в визажисты она/он решила/л податься".
⠀
согласно данным исследования по оценке ситуации в области домашнего насилия, проведенного новак и юнфпа в 2014 году, запрет на учебу, работу либо экономическое насилие распознают как форму насилия 70% женщин и 58% мужчин.
⠀

to have these feelings

text:
women long oppressed globally, stood up for their rights and unfortunately got fooled by the term of women empowerment. 
searching for equality and respect has landed women in shame, exploitation, harassment and made them an object used for selling almost any and every 'thing' & 'service' 
1. you  don't have to be dressing yourself in a manner to show case yourself. women are not public property. respect your body. cover it! 
2. various addictions don't make you cool or hip. they only help men take advantage of you. needless to say what these addictions do to your health

3. working should be your choice not necessity to prove that you are as talented as a male. it should be to make you happy not slog away silently so that you prove you are educated. 
4. don't look down upon women who choose to be homemakers. not many men can do half as good to manage home and they don't try to prove they are good at everything. why do women have to prove anything? 
5. staying out late at nights doesn't make you strong or equal a male. it only gives opportunity to weak uneducated males to commit crimes. stay safe... women empowerment does not mean what the above creative says.. empowerment means to be free to choose and not having to prove your worth while being safe and not be objectified

#women #empowerment #womenempowerement #safety #respect #goodvibes #homemaker #proud #wife #daughter #sister #educated #power #loyal #notanobject #strong #intelligent #smart #metoo #movement

text:
partir avant le levé du soleil. affronter la pénombre. les fantômes ne fuient pas les réverbères. l'angoisse d'une mauvaise rencontre trop fraîche souille le calme de la ville. 
les fantômes sont les animaux humains pour qui la femme n'a pas de voix autre que celle qu'ils désirent.
le ventre lourd de possibles effrayants, les trottoirs s'étirent. peu à peu, en s'approchant de la place, ils se peuplent. la peur reflue. pour un temps, tapie aux fond de mes poches.

la colère pointe son nez.

#journal #agression #metoo #paris #peur #blackandwhitephotography #parismaville
#feministe

text:
on wednesday, 17th october 2018, the women’s development cell at ahmedabad university will host a talk on ‘#metoo #wdc' by dr ranjana harish (former professor and head, department of english, school of languages and director, reaney canadian study centre, gujarat university). addressing issues around gender inequalities and women’s safety, the talk will focus on the need to sensitise the privileged gender/s about the problems of the marginalised. as founder convener of women’s development cell in gujarat university, dr ranjana harish is uniquely qualified to lead the interactive session which seeks to gain from the valuable inputs of the participants and work towards furthering the sensibility of gender equality.

students, faculty members, and friends, save the date.

join us at gict building (lecture theatre 105; 2:15–3:15 pm) to understand how we can work together and contribute to the success of this mammoth task.

text:
an ode to #metoo and to every woman suffering, fighting, surviving, emerging and living:
look outside your castle.
from the dull stairs and washed walls
you'll see a canopy of trees
and a garden of roses.
those roses have thorns
and those trees are a haven to snakes.
but you're a warrior.
you will build your armour
and you will fight the venom with every antidote
that you will always find within you.
let not the snakes make you fret
or fear your ambitions.
ultimately you possess what they don't:
substance apart from venoms.
.
.
.
.

text:
(part 1/3)
disclaimer- some parts of the incident might be disturbing. 
whenever i am asked to describe one of  my least favourite memories as a child, my mind instantly jumps onto this one incident. it’s hard to put incidents like these into words but one must do it because it can happen with anyone, irrespective of the gender and it needs to be talked about more because #timesup. i was about 5 and he must have been in his 20s. he was our relatives’ driver. the distance from my house to my extended family’s house was roughly a 5 minute walk. he used to call me ‘pari’ and tell
me that i was his favourite kid. i used to call him my favourite uncle as well. our entire family had immense trust in him. i had a habit of staying up late at their house after playing and my mom used to pick me up. this one night, she couldn’t. so he was supposed to walk me home. i was extremely sleepy so i went with it. i just wanted to get home and get some sleep. what i thought was a mere 5 minute walk, turned out be the most painful 5 minutes of my life. he started by playing with my fingers and licking them, i thought he was being funny but he slowly went his way up and forcefully tried kissing me, multiple times. i was horrified. i didn’t know what exactly was happening but i knew it was wrong. he then touched me in highly inappropriate ways. i knew it didn’t feel right. i froze and started crying, running towards my house. the gate was tall so i couldn’t reach it. i just kept on sobbing. he came running towards me and said multiple sorries,wiped my face, gave me a chocolate and hushed me. that was the first night as a child i remember i couldn’t sleep. i became absolutely scared of him and he gave me nightmares for months. my mom and everyone questioned my behaviour and sudden dislike towards him but i couldn’t put it in words. i used to run and hide in closet everytime i saw him.this went on for a while until he finally quit his job. i was 7 by now and was just relieved at the fact that i don’t have to face him but inside i was still terrified.
—
#metooindia #unfinishedscribbles #metoo #timesup #speakup #believesurvivors #violenceagainstwomen #stoptheabuse

text:
(part 2/3)
it was only after i grew up and learned about sexual abuse through an article that i realized i had been a victim as well. after he left, there were couple of times i saw him but i stopped running away. i starred at him with utter disgust and completely ignored him and he tried approaching me several times but failed. i slowly started realizing the difference between right and wrong. it took me years to tell this to my mom and she was horrified and extremely sorry but she was happy that i was well and alive. i have never told this to anyone else besides her and a couple of close friends and family. i know i am definitely not the only one in this and i know that it wasn’t my fault. •
that is just one of the multiple incidents that i can recall. another one that happened to me was on facebook when i added this guy who went to our rival school. it began with the usual hi’s and hello’s until one time he ended up sending me an unsolicited picture of his genitalia. i was too naive and kept on wondering how could someone send their naked pictures to someone they’ve just met. to my horror, my mom found about it and went ballistic. i was petrified and utterly confused. i immediately blocked him without saying a word. i thought he was just being a creep. after that, two of the guys i ended up liking turned out to be the biggest jerks. one of them called me names because things went sour with our so called friendship and the other one falsely accused me of engaging in inappropriate acts just for his “fun” and because it made him laugh. there have been a lot of times where i’ve been called names right in front of my face and the countless number of inappropriate comments lying in my “other” facebook messages folder and direct messages,full of desperate men. •
#unfinishedscribbles #metoo #metooindia #timesup #stoptheabuse #speakup #violenceagainstwomen

text:
you may write me down in history⁣⁣
with your bitter, twisted lies,⁣⁣
you may trod me in the very dirt⁣⁣
but still, like dust, i'll rise...⁣
⁣⁣
🔜 trust your work + defend your truth. tonight was a lovely, intimate gathering of friends and strangers, artists and doulas and foragers and comics and moms and singers and thespians and more. it was a small group. it was @femaissance at her purest. it was healing. it was wholesome. it was intimate. it was low-key. it was lovely. it was what i needed. i named #femaissance in a coffee shop just 2 days after today one year ago-after i decided to also profess #metoo. i owe the success of this project to so many, but i know for certain this day irrevocably readjusted my worldview and set me on the path of truth and standing up for what’s right, no matter the cost. 🔜⁣⁣
⁣⁣
...did you want to see me broken?⁣⁣
bowed head and lowered eyes?⁣⁣
shoulders falling down like teardrops,⁣⁣
weakened by my soulful cries?⁣⁣
⁣⁣
does my haughtiness offend you?⁣⁣
don't you take it awful hard⁣⁣
’cause i laugh like i've got gold mines⁣⁣
diggin’ in my own backyard...⁣
⁣
#mayaangelou #metoo

text: to all my survivors reading this, i just want to take the time to say i’m so proud of you. i’m sorry for what you went through but know you are strong even when it doesn’t feel like it. if you need proof, just think that you are here reading this and we support you. because that’s what we do. as survivors we believe and support one another. ive learned it’s okay to have countless moments when all you want to do is cry or your angry or confused and i’m telling you all of these emotions are okay and don’t let anyone’s else’s opinions convince you otherwise. #metoo ❤️ -rissy  #love #youareenough #loveyourselffirst #quotes #quotesdaily #inspiration #sexualassault #empowerment  #survivor #metoo #metoomovement #quitthisshit #recovery #feminist #feminism #feministquote  #trauma #female #inspirationalquote #equality #trigger #triggerwarning #assault #ptsd #mybodymychoice #consent #endrapeculture #timesup

text:
(part 3/3)
i’ve talked to my peers about sexual harassment and their carefree attitude appalls me. the fact that most of the women have been victimized at some point or the other in their lives, and yet they choose to neglect it, infuriates me. we’ve been so conditioned to behave in a certain way just because we’re girls, that we’ve given a way to normalize sexual misconduct because “log kya kahenge” and worse if it’s on social media because that’s not “real harassment”. our conditioned mindset is the reason why we as victims have been blaming ourselves and this is exactly why need a movement like #metoo. it isn’t just a plethora of women sharing their stories. it’s about coming together and standing up against the overdue abuse that we’re forced to endure, even though my heart breaks thinking about how restricted we’ve been that we needed a movement to share our stories. in the recent wake of #metoo, i have read about millions of comments asking the victims about what took them so long to speak up. and that nobody cares, because they could be making this up falsely for purely attention seeking reasons. first of all, each person processes pain differently. sexual abuse is not just physical or limited to the cyberspace. it’s about the mental torture and struggle that the victim goes through. there is a multi-layered healing process that can take as long as a lifetime to overcome the pain and torture. it’s about dealing with the shame, the shock and the courage to speak out. it’s not something you do for attention. secondly, people do tend to over react and misuse the law without even realizing it. if someone is speaking about how they felt uncomfortable in a relationship, you’ve no right to deny or call them out just because it doesn’t “meet the guidelines of #metoo”. the movement is not an institution, its not gender specific, it’s about standing up to the society and telling them that we’re done with their shit and brave enough to call them out on it. so i request the people reading this  to be more kind because that’s the least you can do, without judging the victims. you don’t know it until you go through it. —
#unfinishedscribbles #metoo #metooindia

text:
i've got excuses a plenty. *my mom is in town!!! *tired from work *ladyness cramps *kids need help getting tasks done *it's late
*i want donuts *did i mention my mom is here?!?!?!? i could let things get in the way. but folks, life happens!! we can use every excuse in the book..but, when you start wanting it for yourself bad enough... when you keep the promises you make to yourself... when you know that taking care of yourself makes it easier to take care of others... that's when you visit with your mom while you chisel your shoulders :) you don't have to choose. you can have & do all the things. and eat the donuts too ;) #youareenough #selflove #bodylove #selfcare #juststart #loveyourself #metoo #lovemymom #creatingabettermeforme #andforthem #onwardandupward

text:
the artist part 1: to all my human beings out there: 👥👥👥 this weekend i was privileged to be a part of a collaboration that was brought about by recent public statements made regarding the appointment of brett kavanaugh to the supreme court in spite of allegations of violent sexual assault. the president released a public statement apologizing for brett kavanaugh’s experience and the statement, “it’s a hard time to be a man.” so many are touched by sexual assault and abuse that go unprotected and unheard. this is a terrifying and painful reality that is absolutely everyone’s problem.

#abuse #abusesurvivor #domesticabuse #abuseawareness #verbalabuse #sexualabuse #mentalabuse #abuserecovery #arttherapy #hardtimetobe  #nomeansno #metoo #whyididntreport #endviolence @hardtimetobe @you_are_not_crazy @abuse_warriors @pcatennessee @narcissist.sociopath.awarenes2 @emotional_abuse_recovery @narcissist.sociopath.awarenes2 @narcissistic_abuse @narcissistic_abuse_is_real @narcopathawareness @childabusememorial @been_there_got_out @i_was_abused_emotionaly @case_of_the_ex @abusesurvivorsunite @bikersagainstchildabuseintl @narcandempath @sexualabusesurvivorsstories @sexualabuse.awareness @sexual.abuse.survivor @sexualabusesupportgroup @sexualabusehelp

text:
what comes after #metoo ?
.
the past couple of weeks have been traumatic for all of us. the biggest revelation was also, how many people were not aware that they were being harassed, how many have carried someone else’s shame as their own for years. this is the nature of harassment; that somewhere you might think it was your fault. aside from calling out predators, we need to also now work together to make sure that there is a safer environment moving forward. 
remember, there is strength in sharing and there is safety in numbers. @tessjoseph19 has started exactly this initiative. do fill out the form. it is entirely confidential, and asks you to name nobody. (cut and paste the link below)
.
and please know, whatever it is, it’s not your fault. .

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1auomkuy62j6tw-oti6szgrdjzi7obrnch4d0lpooti0/viewform?edit_requested=true

text:
i stitched this while contemplating the word "no". i used to have a t-shirt, bright red and in white block letters was the word "no". that shirt got me a lot of male attention. one man after another would ask "no what?" some of them would ask as we interacted about something else,  some would approach me out of nowhere to ask what my shirt meant. as i continued to stitch, it occurred to me when these men asked the question, their tones varied. some asked playfully, some confused, but most of the time their tone wasn't inquisitive. the majority didn't ask me a question so much as demand an answer - "no what?" no permission? no access? no thank you? just no? 
the very existence of "no" was foreign to them, offensive even. "no" just wasn't on their radar, so the minute they detected it- beep beep beep here they came running, demanding to know what exactly it was they were being denied. 
i find this very telling. even more telling is the fact that i never had to explain to a  woman what my shirt meant. not one ever asked. 
#handembroidery #embroidery #threadtherapy #threadhead #hoophoe #metoo #nomeansno #malefragility #maletears #stitchtober day 15

text:
jennifer part 2: it’s an uncomfortable topic, and i see so many people who don’t understand what it feels like to be dehumanized on that level, outwardly judging people and what they’ve gone through. sexual assault is a crime against humanity, and i think it’s devastatingly sad to see our country’s leader openly trying to invalidate multiple, credible women’s stories to serve his political agenda. whatever happened to justice, and protecting the innocent? it’s time for more of us to speak up about this, because it isn’t just a problem for victims, but it’s everyone’s problem. what if it was you, or someone you loved?

it’s heartbreakingly sad for me to say that i’ve been a victim of sexual assault on multiple occasions. i need to be open with all of you about exactly what those experiences, and the aftermath felt like.

helpless. gripped with fear. deeply shamed. worthless. voiceless. sick. isolated from others. damaged, like a lesser human being. inferior, like nothing i could ever do would make me whole again, or even equal to others. humiliated. bound to silence. dishonored. i felt like no one would ever understand. i have suffered in silence for a long time. i have had suicidal thoughts. i have struggled for years trying to prove to others i had worth, trying to be good enough because of this underlying fear that who i am isn’t enough. i have experienced the deepest level of shame and depression. i have blamed myself. i thought maybe this evil, dehumanizing behavior of another is somehow my fault. i have had so much to overcome. these experiences have attacked the core of who i am.

text_retweet:
repost @lukemclean__ 
why is it that we see being sad or crying as being weak? “i have to be strong” “i need to be tough”

why? 🤷🏻‍♂️ being upset or sad is an emotion and i feel like we live in a society now that is trying to ban being sad, we label it as weakness and we create a world where we have to be positive all the time. 
did you know...? crying can reduce emotional stress and if left unchecked it can cause increased risk of cardiovascular disease and other related disorders. 
it’s okay to feel certain emotions and it’s okay to cry, in fact... it’s healthy!

text:
jennifer part 3: this is really just a short snapshot of the experiences, and what i went through after that. by sharing my story, i want others to know just how evil and damaging sexual assault is. it shouldn’t be a common experience. it shouldn’t be joked about or laughed at. what if it was you? i want people to fight to protect and honor those who weren’t protected. i want people to speak up. i want to be fought for, and i want to fight for others. 
this photo is a part of a collaboration to bring awareness to this issue, .... this photo is a part of a collaboration to bring awareness to this issue. if you or someone you know wants to be a part of this body of work (replicating the image of being bound with duct tape/wearing a red tie), please reach out to me, my friend @carolinenicolehaag or @kevinirelan 
every voice matters.

text: you don’t have to be a woman, you don’t have to have a sister, you don’t have to have a daughter.. to be a decent human being and respect women. it’s not what we wear, is not how we walk. it’s you, you make the choice to respect women or not. you are making a conscious choice by voting for woman’s rights and making sure that our future generations have equality. that no boy grows up thinking he has ownership over a woman’s body. that no girl has to live her attacks over and over again wondering what she did wrong. you’re making the choice. i’ve never had to say #metoo but it doesn’t mean i will sit back and watch the show. #resist #votethemout  #countryoverparty ♥️ #womensrights #equality

text: a rough draft of something i want to make. it's from ecclesiastes 3:7, and i feel like it's something sexual abuse survivors need to hear. do not feel shamed for not telling when it happened, whether it was years ago or days ago. there are reasons we don't tell. it's your experience and your story to share when you are ready. i pray that when you do speak, you would be surrounded by those who will hear you, come alongside you, believe you, and help you decide what steps you are ready to take towards healing. #metoo #churchtoo #handlettered #handlettering #leftylettering #leftyletterer #leftycalligraphers #ecclesiastes #moderncalligraphy

text:
jennifer part 1: the person i want to be is authentic, honest, and courageous. while those are some of my deepest values, the truth is that sometimes it’s hard to speak up, and bring that level of transparency to a social media platform, especially when it’s something so deeply personal, and has been a source of emotional pain for me for a long time.

when the #metoo movement started, i wanted to post something because i’m a part of that group, but i didn’t want the importance of my story to be diminished in any way, because of just how common it was becoming to see these posts from people in my facebook friend groups. the sad part of it is exactly that--that it’s becoming such a common experience, which means it’s becoming such a big big problem. turning a blind eye to injustice is wrong. 
there are many people i talk to who are flippant about those experiences and think the victim is just trying to get attention, or ruin another person’s life, or that their experience is somehow invalid. this is a pretty ignorant perspective to take, especially when it takes so much courage to speak up in the first place. 
#abuse #abusesurvivor #domesticabuse #abuseawareness #verbalabuse #sexualabuse #mentalabuse #abuserecovery #arttherapy #hardtimetobe  #nomeansno #metoo #whyididntreport #endviolence @hardtimetobe @you_are_not_crazy @abuse_warriors @pcatennessee @narcissist.sociopath.awarenes2 @emotional_abuse_recovery @narcissist.sociopath.awarenes2 @narcissistic_abuse @narcissistic_abuse_is_real @narcopathawareness @childabusememorial @been_there_got_out @i_was_abused_emotionaly @case_of_the_ex @abusesurvivorsunite @bikersagainstchildabuseintl @narcandempath @sexualabusesurvivorsstories @sexualabuse.awareness @sexual.abuse.survivor @sexualabusesupportgroup @sexualabusehelp

pre_proc_tweet:
from  -  when i decided to run for the senate in 2012, i never thought that my family’s native american heritage would come under attack and my dead parents would be called liars. and i never expected the president of the united states to use my family’s story as a racist political joke against native american history, culture, and people – over, and over, and over.

but you know me: i don’t take any fight lying down, so today we launched a new fact squad website for anyone who wants see the facts for themselves.

text:
#페미니즘... #양성평등... #젠더...
.
학사 논문 쓰면서 뭐 그렇게 요란스럽냐고 하지만 방송대를 다닌다는 거 자체만으로도 나 스스로 참 요란스러운거 같음 ㅎ 사실상 위 세 주제는 방송대 다니면서 배우게 된 부분. 저 세 단어가 나의 학사 졸업 소논문 주제...;;; 어쩌다보니 ㅎ
.
한국사회는 우선 이슈가 먼저 터지고난 뒤에 제도적 뒷받침을 이끌어내는? 이상한 사회구조라 '차별금지법'안으로 인해 동성애자를 인정하느냐 마느냐의 문제들이 법안때문에 드러나게 되고 그제서야 찬반토론을 하고 있는...
.
젠더교육에 대해 배우기도 하고 이번 소논문 주제도 그렇게 잡고 있긴 하지만... 크리스천으로서의 젠더교육(차별문제)에 대해 어떻게 접근해야 할지...
.
난 페미니스트도 아니고, 능력에 의한 성차별에 대해서 깊이있게 생각해본 적도 없는데 이번 논문 쓰다가 사회운동가 되는거 아닌가 싶음 ㅋ 뭐 지금도 충분히 사회운동가적 모습은 보이고 있지만...
.
세상을 변화시킨다는 건 결국 작은 불씨 하나로 인한 거니까. 최근 발의된 '윤창호법'도 비슷한 거니까...
.
'여자라는 이름으로'의 영화 예고편만 봤는데 저렇게까지 싸울 수 있는 용기를 낸다는 것이 대단한 것 같다. 최근 미투운동도 그렇고 말이지...
.
논문 자료 검색하다가 열받아서 어디선가 소리소리 지르고 있을지도 ㅎㅎ 의외로 남녀차별이 넘쳐나는 곳이 교회라는 사실을 알고 더 분노하고 있는 중이라서 ㅋ  예를 들면 목회자의 아내를 '사모'라는 웃기는 '직함'으로 직업화? 한다는거..
.
나 자신이 먼저 젠더교육이 잘 되기 위해서 쓰는 글이니 나중에 어디선가 페미니즘 교육을 하고 있는 나를 발견한다면... ㅋ 진짜 웃길듯 ㅋㅋ  이러다 진짜 교육학자 되겠다고 하는거 아닌가 몰라..
.
방송대에서 교육학 공부한 건 가고싶은 대학원이 있어서 그 전에 학사를 끝내려고 시작한건데 공부하다보니 대학원 진학 생각이 사라짐;;; 학사공부 자체만으로도 넘나 힘든 시간이어서... ㅠ 왠지 방송대 청소년학과를 편입할 거 같다는 느낌적인 느낌은 있음 ㅋ
.
#여자라는이름으로 #이탈리아영화 #metoo #응원합니다

'여자라는 이름으로'의 영화 예고편만 봤는데 저렇게까지 싸울 수 있는 용기를 낸다는 것이 대단한 것 같다. 최근 미투운동도 그렇고 말이지...
.
논문 자료 검색하다가 열받아서 어디선가 소리소리 지르고 있을지도 ㅎㅎ 의외로 남녀차별이 넘쳐나는 곳이 교회라는 사실을 알고 더 분노하고 있는 중이라서 ㅋ  예를 들면 목회자의 아내를 '사모'라는 웃기는 '직함'으로 직업화? 한다는거..
.
나 자신이 먼저 젠더교육이 잘 되기 위해서 쓰는 글이니 나중에 어디선가 페미니즘 교육을 하고 있는 나를 발견한다면... ㅋ 진짜 웃길듯 ㅋㅋ  이러다 진짜 교육학자 되겠다고 하는거 아닌가 몰라..
.
방송대에서 교육학 공부한 건 가고싶은 대학원이 있어서 그 전에 학사를 끝내려고 시작한건데 공부하다보니 대학원 진학 생각이 사라짐;;; 학사공부 자체만으로도 넘나 힘든 시간이어서... ㅠ 왠지 방송대 청소년학과를 편입할 거 같다는 느낌적인 느낌은 있음 ㅋ
.

text:
red trauma,  mix media on canvas , 2013
.
.
abuse is any child’s worst nightmare; physical abuse can wound human soul terribly when it comes with sexual assault. my work is about such experiences which i have lived through every day once when it was happening and now when it has happened. i paint self-portraits as my catharsis, i have tried words earlier but this has served me more than any medium. it’s a cage of my own self which never let me out. it’s not only me; it’s every other person in different prison of inner self hiding others’ mistakes. i have lived through it and will be breathing through it. all that dirt poured on my soul was not mine, how it could be; i was just a child, i was ‘she’. my work is a narration of my emotional struggle being a survivor of sexual abuse mainly. it is a statement about psychological and emotional impact of abuse on children as well as adults. our social taboos does not allow women as well as men to raise a voice about their sufferings which makes it more suffocating. we don't have a way out of this because we don't have any one to listen or understand. .
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
blue trauma, mix media on canvas,  2013
.
.
abuse is any child’s worst nightmare; physical abuse can wound human soul terribly when it comes with sexual assault. my work is about such experiences which i have lived through every day once when it was happening and now when it has happened. i paint self-portraits as my catharsis, i have tried words earlier but this has served me more than any medium. it’s a cage of my own self which never let me out. it’s not only me; it’s every other person in different prison of inner self hiding others’ mistakes. i have lived through it and will be breathing through it. all that dirt poured on my soul was not mine, how it could be; i was just a child, i was ‘she’. my work is a narration of my emotional struggle being a survivor of sexual abuse mainly. it is a statement about psychological and emotional impact of abuse on children as well as adults. our social taboos does not allow women as well as men to raise a voice about their sufferings which makes it more suffocating. we don't have a way out of this because we don't have any one to listen or understand. .
.

text:
no 🐺 in this narrative 🔪 lol. like my boy @xthirdeyeaestheticsx 👏🏻would say: protect yourself. jokes apart, can’t deny that pop culture, cinema and the primarily the premise of porn (which sadly for a lot of us, has been a reference point to how intimacy looks like) monetises on, if not promoting; than glamorising philandry, unsafe sex, #toxicmasculinity, unhealthy beauty standards, distrust and more than ever violence. where resistance from the partner, is mistaken for approval and the plot progresses with the victim succumbing to the abuser 😒. no wonder it desensitises the brain, and the lines between ‘real life’ and ‘reel life’ get trespassed. and the ramifications are increasingly being felt globally in form of #metoo campaigns and wide coverage of #maritalrape and sexual misconduct in work environments. i might get flack for saying this, but in the current dating climate, #sexpositivity has snowballed into some precariously oblivious ‘millennial movement’ of sorts. and with this unloading of angst towards the common public and familial discourse, that of #victimblaming. especially in this geographical landscape where #morality is a twisted concept and discussing #sexualhealth is blasphemy. guess the only point i’m pushing for is — that even when you’re taking shots on the playing field, educate yourself about #consent. acknowledge that consent is mandatory. and essentially, understand the implications of “yes” and “no”. ➡️ sharing screen grabs from a story by @theyoungturks on #rapeculture from youtube, also a wonderfully written @teenvogue article on enthusiastic consent and episode 22 on #pornaddiction and how it effects relationships, from my current favourite podcast series @loveumentary by @bigbags ft. @fightthenewdrug. all of which i find to be credible resources. k byeeeeeeeeeeee.
~

text:
zainab salbi @zainabsalbi , an iraqi human-right activist, founded women for women international, a grassroots humanitarian and development organization dedicated to serving women survivors of war while she was only 23 year old. under her leadership as the organization’s ceo (1993-2011), women for women international grew from helping 30 women when it first started to more than 400,000 women in 8 conflict areas.
in october 2015, salbi launched the nida’a show, a groundbreaking talk show dedicated to addressing and inspiring women in the arab world, and she recently launched a new show ”#metoo, now what?”
we proudly follow zainab and encourage you to do the same!  #arabfeminists

text:
i don’t recognize the girl on left...
she was sick, she was sad, she was broken, she was lost... mostly tho, she was drinking...
***trigger warning ⚠️ ****
a lot has changed in the last 2.5 years, &not my weight (believe it or not, i weigh the same in both photos).
i decided i needed to heal, and started to make changes, i got off anti depressant/anxiety meds, which i had been on for 6 years(i felt really ready and talked to my doctors, it’s not recommended for everyone). i decided that i needed to really dig down deep to start healing, and altho those meds were helpful, they didn’t help heal me. 
ive dealt with darkness my whole life... having a fatal disease, and being told by doctors at a very young age i didn’t have much of chance of seeing my 18th birthday was always hard, i spent a lot of time in hospital, i missed a lot of school and often kids were cruel, they didn’t want to be friends with a kid who was sick. 
but i suffered a major trauma at 22, i was a virgin and was drugged and raped.
shortly after sank down into a very very dark place. i went through trauma therapy, and counselling, which was helpful. but it wasn’t until about 2 years ago that i started talking about it with other women who had also been through sexual trauma that i actually started to heal.
because nothing sends you down into darkness faster than feeling utterly alone in something you’ve experienced...and nothing more uplifting and freeing then realizing you’re not alone. 
i realized that my heavy drinking needed to stop... it was killing me, body and soul. 
so i cut back, a lot. 
it wasn’t until i got together with my loving, supportive and sober partner @mccaffreym2 that i really was able to kick the habit. it’s really incredible what having a good support system will do for the healing process. 
all that being said, not everyone has that special person in their lives...and i’d like to extend a hand, to anyone struggling, who wants to change or wants to heal. i’m here for you. it’s not easy, to be honest it’s scary as hell. but nothing is more worth it. it’s incredible what happens, the light that start to stream in when you decide to step out of the darkness.
#metoo

text:
time for some rather long oversharing, my hands are sweating as i type this. it's been a year since the #metoo movement went viral in the wake of the weinstein case, over ten years after first being launched by activist tarana burke. one year later things haven't gotten much better, particularly given the confirmation of brett kavanaugh. i don't quite have the words for how incredibly distressing this all has been. i've only recently made the decision to take the first steps of sharing my stories. recently, @amandapalmer and jasmine power released a video for their song 'mr. weinstein will see you now' (which i greatly encourage you to watch and listen to). it greatly inspired me to start creating some very vaunerable art surrounding my experiences and existing in my body as a survivor. i wanted to use motifs prevalent in the video because watching it for the first time was such an intensely cathartic and empowering experience and i don't think i've ever connected to another piece of art like that. 
if you've read this far, thank you. 
more to come, as i am planning a new series on the subject.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
enquanto ela deseja que esses problemas tenham se resolvidos por ora, nos #metoo clima de hoje, aguilera está reconfortada em saber que suas músicas ainda funcionam para seus fãs. "nessa maneira é ótimo como essas mensagens ainda são atemporais e fortes nos dias de hoje." diz ela.
para não dizer que tudo na sua vida continuou o mesmo. enquanto aguilera diz "eu nunca serei aquela que foge da sua idade", a cantora de 37 anos ri quando relembra alguns dos jeitos interessantes que ela sente sobre sua idade. por exemplo, somente agora, ela diz, que está pagando o preço pela sua turnê anterior. naquela época, uma espontânea de 27 anos usou "um salto spiked de 5 centímetros sem protetores de calcanhar e disse, 'ah, eu vou conseguir lidar com isso quando eu estiver mais velha.'" mesmo uma década depois, seus pés sentem as repercussões. aguilera ri e diz, "está voltando a me assombrar agora!". .
.
while she wishes more of these issues had been resolved by now, in today’s #metoo climate, aguilera is comforted in knowing her songs still work for her fans. “in that way it’s great how timeless and strong those messages still are today,” she said.
that’s not to say everything in her life has remained the same. while aguilera said “i’ll never be one that shies away from my age,” the 37-year-old laughs as she recalls some of the interesting ways she’s feeling her age. for example, only now, she said, is she paying the price for her previous tour. back then, a spontaneous 27-year-old wore “5-inch spiked heels with no comfort pads and said, ‘oh, i’ll deal with it when i get older.’ ” even a decade later, her feet are feeling the repercussions. aguilera laughs and says, “it’s coming back to haunt me now!” - chicago tribune

text:
creating controversial content is never easy.  it is not meant to be. controversial conversations involve confronting issues, sometimes these issues are unsavory and culturally pertinent. 
over the last 48 hours several women have expressed that our micro-short while a tribute to broken home lands and religious turmoil, reminds them of the violence women experience in these countries and how we hide under the blanket of “cultural normalcy” when we fail to get involved or help individuals experiencing domestic violence or sexual harrasment
.
as the #metooindia movement finally surfaces, i as an american- indian woman, ask of my internet friends, that you stop allowing violence and atrocities towards any gender because you feel the culture deems it appropriate or normal.  do not let your brothers, sisters, mothers, fathers, children and friends suffer because an antiquated society has taught you too
.
be brave. unlearn and speak up
@suswana_sohinee .

text:
from last few days , there is something in me which is disturbing me a-lot ! i promised myself not to dive in more but i could not resist . .
.
.
the stories of #metoo is heart-wrecking . corporate sexual abuse or industry favour molestation or family ‘shut your abuse’ program . 
in all above i find just one glitch - upbringing 
these people are mentally ill , socially powerful and devoid of humanity .
stories of @redheadwayfarer , @sandymridul and others @metoo_in made me think again that these woman are super strong to talk about it with dignity to help other silent #metoo survivers . thankyou for talking on behalf of us .
.
. 🎗as a parent , a mother of a boy its so significant and a responsibility to make my son learn how to respect every woman around him at various stage in life ! 
let our kids be more morally reformed , sensitive and more human to create safe society . .
.
📍for now , we need to support all the voices coming out and respect the one who choose not be vocal enough in public .

i hope power should not supersede humanity in #metoo .
.
whats your thought ?? pls comment  and share the post as a gesture of supporting the movement . .
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
as a survivor of sexual abuse at the age of 5 and rape at 14, i would like to salute all those that have spoken up and plan on doing so. i know it is very difficult to do it because i have been there and it took me many years to be able to talk about it. it takes immense amount of courage to share this with the world. it’s even harder when you tell those that are close to you and they are supposed to protect you, yet they do nothing. i have been there too and it hurts like hell. but i want these survivors to know it is truly liberating and completely worth it. do not let the nonbelievers stop you. this is your truth. do not ever be afraid to speak your truth. do not let this opportunity pass you. this is a moment that has been long overdue for all of us. this is your chance to be heard and finally obtain justice. i believe you.
.
.
.
.
#metoo #ibelieveyou #somyali #speakup #shoutitout #iamwithyou #survivors #truth #takeastand #staystrong #wecandoit #justice #longoverdue #pakistan #india #bollywood

text:
ajeeb baat hay, bachpan se he shaadi k liye tyaar karna shuru kar daitay hain, khana banana, safai rakhna, uthnay aur baithnay ka saleeka, apne shohar ka khyaal rakhna, lekin kabhi koi jinsi taluqaat k baray mein toh kuch nahin batata. kuch batana bhi nahin, aur khud se seekhna bhi nahin. porn, ghalat baat! mills & boon novels, ghalat baat! practice, matlab maut.
when in school, a teacher overheard us talking about sex, as a consequence we were sent to the headmistress’s office, there, we were forced to write an apology on a pink paper which went into our files and was later shown to our parents. an apology? for having a healthy discussion about sex? amongst friends? aaj tak kuch samajh nahin ayi. i hated my school, its administration, their rules were arbitrary and humiliation was used as a form of punishment. we were humiliated for crossing the ground to meet the boys on the other side, for talking to them, sitting with them, for having any sort of contact with them and yet a course called ethics (wuttt) was introduced to the girls section to prepare us for them, for marriage. this course taught us many things: how to sit, how to eat, how to wear a dupatta, how to bake, how to fold napkins, how to make a bed, all of which i unlearnt. wife 101 would’ve been a more appropriate name for the course, how to be the perfect wife without ever having sex. nobody educated us about sex, let alone non consensual sex. nobody talked about rape or molestation or any kind of sexual harassment. 
our mothers used to say, ‘koi bhi haath lagaye, chahe mard ho ya aurat, toh humein ah kar batana,’ but since our school made us feel so ashamed of having any contact with the opposite sex, we figured, to avoid humiliation, it would be best if we remained quiet about the man who squeezed our breasts, and the man who groped our butts, and the man who grabbed our vaginas. #metoo yaar. 
acha, khair, baat yeh nahin thi, baat yeh thi keh schools ko sex education shuru kar daini chaiye. itni koi sharam ki baat nahin. ethics type courses per ziada sharmindagi honi chaiye. aur agar schools yeh initiative nahin laitay, toh maa baap ko laina chaiye.

text:
#notesformyboys.
.
it is impossible to live in this #metoo era and not turn my eyes to the boys i have running around my house. i’m examining more carefully what they say about what they learn at school, their perceptions from church, their books and media. what is it saying about men and women? what are they learning about the nature of human relationships? what are the messages here about masculinity? i bought two notebooks today, one for each of them, a place to jot down these notes that one day hopefully they will read.
.
dear sons, trust is earned. you are not entitled to it because of your: position, ability, intelligence, gender, money, (fill in the blank). love you, mum

text:
today i spoke with @jameelajamilofficial about her @i_weigh initiative, which i love more than anything! this is something each of you can be a part of and i hope you will be.

this is a movement which aims to tackle the relentless focus on women's weight, which is used to  define who they are and their worth in the world. 
each of you can take part by sharing your real value in a post like this. imagine if we start to see ourselves as we really are rather than numbers on a scale. bravo to all the women who are a part of this ❤️🙌 please start sharing what you weigh we all really want to know 😉! ❤️🙌👏#iweigh a lot

#fact : 💜domestic abuse is a huge problem. it is estimated that 1 in 4 women live in abusive relationships, and within our lifetime half of us can expect to be the victim of domestic or intimate violence. abuse can be lethal. more women are killed by their partner or ex-partner than by a stranger. and even where physical violence has not occurred, the emotional scars can often have a lifelong effect on the victim.

the lyrics to the song “all too well” by taylor swift always remind me of the months before i moved in with my abuser, so here’s a poem about that. 
during that time, my abuser’s parents were always out of town and we spent a lot of time alone at their house, pretending like we were living together, and the things that happened really foreshadowed what was to come. —————
*this is a repost of a poem i posted then deleted yesterday because it needed editing* ———————————————————————-

text:
“if they fall, they will not stay down, because the lord will help them up.” psalms 37:24
📖
get it, girl! this is part of "day 7", "she is fam"  from our free 7-day devotional /declaration for abuse survivors! it’s scary living with abuse. as much as we put on the facade that we’re okay and put on a smiling face, on the inside we’re conflicted. confused. hurt. angry. sad. why did we have to get hurt? to be honest, i don’t know the answer to that. we live in a fallen world. a very troubled one in fact. none of us leave this earth unscathed. unfortunately. but you’ve survived.
👊🏽
you’ve made it out. you’ve been through it and now you’re on the other side...so what now? as we’ve discussed through the past week, where you find your identity is crucial. what or who you place your identity in has the power to control you. and that seat in your life should only be occupied by god. and even then, god doesn’t want to control you. he wants to heal, give you identity, purpose, and have a relationship with you. he wants to take your surviving and turn it into thriving. amen!?👇🏽
{for the rest of this free encouraging devotional, click the link in our bio!}
.
.
.

text:
tell your story. 
shout it. write it. 
whisper it if you have to. 
but tell it. 
some won't understand it. 
some will outright reject it. 
but many will 
thank you for it. 
and then the most
magical thing will happen. 
one by one, voices will start 
whispering, 'me, too.'
and your tribe will gather. 
and you will never 
feel alone again.

text: i was trying, in these days before the election, to find a symbol that would express my caring, my outrage, my commitment. lacking time to knit (i’m giving my time to working on political mailings), i thought of this: a safety pin, symbol of caring and standing up for each other; a woman symbol, in the wake of kavanaugh’s confirmation, a way to express solidarity with women finding the courage to speak out; a cat, symbol of our resistance to a corrupt and cruel administration. $6, ($5 if i can give it to you in person in bloomington, indiana) with $1 going to planned parenthood, $1 to middle way house, our local center for abused women. paypal me at lshifriss(at)yahoo(dot)com and include your address if necessary. #resist #metoo #metoomovement

text:
as many of you all know or may not know i am a survivor of #sexualabuse. however, this  post is not about my story.  this is about @katiemeyler and her non profit organization @morethanme. this very topic is what i am dedicating my life to. the culture of liberian men sleeping or abusing young children is prevalent (almost normal) that many of us are told to keep quiet, move on, forgive and forget. at this time i refuse to keep quiet. i’ll move on with my voice loud. i’ll forgive but never forget. 
more than me your vision of “every girl empowered” is flawed. your mission of protecting children is not exemplified through your actions and the true insensitivity to what has happened to these girls before and after coming in contact with you. you had a relationship with a man who abused/raped and infected girls who you were set to protect.  you obtained millions and millions of dollars at the expense of the innocence of girls. you persuaded millions of people to donate at the cost of many girls getting aids. you manipulated girls into thinking you could save them from the streets but gave them false hope. your greed allowed you to keep these girls in a cycle of sexual exploitation. you promised to make your dream come true at the detriment of generations. you temporarily stepped down but the lives of these girls will be changed forever 
but what about the government? what about the people of the country. children are the hope for the future but why are they not protected ? why is sexual abuse swept under the rug? why in the african community is seeking help a sign of weakness. why are the victims/ survivors frowned upon but never the abuser. why is the more than me foundation still running under the same board of directors. what is the plan? the co-founder and it’s board must go before the law. 
i pray these survivors find the strength to continue to be bold. to be free and heal their wounds. i’m asking for everyone to join me in prayer to keep the victims and their families lifted as this is a trying time in their lives. i pray that the government will prevail and justice will be served. lord i ask that these survivors find peace within you. ❤️

text:
sign the pledge!!! girlstoo.girlsinc.org today, on the anniversary of #metoo going viral, girls inc. is proud to announce the launch of a new campaign called #girlstoo. this national campaign will focus on sexual harassment and assault in the lives of youth, particularly girls, with actions aimed at changing the norms and stereotypes that fuel these behaviors.

respect starts young. from an early age, young people receive limiting and harmful messages about how girls and boys should behave and be treated. one in four girls is the victim of sexual violence by age 18, and 7 in 10 girls are sexually harassed in high school.

girls alone cannot fix this - nor should they have to. it’s going to take each and every one of us. the problem is vast but change is achievable.

girls alone cannot fix this - nor should they have to. it’s going to take each and every one of us. the problem is vast but change is achievable.

meet @amandangocnguyen, ceo and founder of @risenow.us, a multi-sector coalition of sexual assault survivors and allies working to empower all survivors with civil rights. amanda penned her own civil rights into existence and unanimously passed the sexual assault survivors’ bill of rights after having to navigate the broken criminal justice system following the injustices she faced after being raped. 11 other laws protecting sexual violence survivors have been created modeled off of her federal law. we're excited to team up with amanda, @obeygiant and @risenow.us to bring our art and accompanying lesson plans outlining paths to real world action to 20,000 or more schools during the 2018/2019 school year. support our next generation of leaders and contribute to #wethefuturenow by visiting the link in our header.
