text:
i have three daughters and i worry so much about them, particularly in this current political climate. i used to sing this song to them (from babe): “if i had words to make a day for you, 
i'd sing you a morning golden & true
i would make this day last for all time 
then fill the night deep in moonshine.” 🌖🌕🌔
alas, the best i can do is love them and add #distressedfx filters to photos of them to make the world look a little more magical. #daughter #daughterlove #metoo #owenbeach #naturemedicine

text: 1 in 4 women will suffer at least one miscarriage, i  personally know over 25 women who have, including myself.  yet it is taboo to talk about.  the hardest part is moving on from something that has no understanding or solid  object of blame. how one week your little peanut can have a steady and strong heart beat and the next week your womb is empty.  how you can go to an appointment on a friday and sunday night deliver a still born.  there is no name for women/men who loose a child because the devastation of such a lost can not be captioned.  the worst part is not knowing why or how it keeps happening. i  coped by doing research  on hormones in the long term affects of birth control  and other things that make women vulnerable to miscarriages. so today we take time to  bring awareness and continue to  advocate, as we remember those sweet angels  i’m advocating for the mothers who has lost  and living with the ongoing sense of pain .for  fathers that feels that lost double because essentially looses a baby and a part of his wife or partner. may you be blessed  with the numbing power of laughter and love of your other children.  #doula #comadres  #metoo #jmt.5 #8/19/12
name: Haydee salas Taylor CD(DONA)

text: this week i started my life fresh and weights lifted. i cannot express my complete rejuvenation and joy to have shackles broken free. today i was invited to put my hand print on the wall at the carousel center, along with dozens of other children that went through childhood abuse and others fighting it. it takes a village! today i had big discussion about the process in north carolina for survivors and children. next stop is county commissioners. i’m excited to work to make changes further. i feel blessed to have freedom of speech, and so far been invited to have a voice within this community. i look forward to working with the carousel center, alliance for children’s rights los angeles, and the commissioner to try and make changes for the best. #childrensadvocacy #stoptheabuse #giveback #metoo #saveourchildren #supportyourcommunity #newhanovercounty #northcarolina

text:
day 19.  still no contact.  waiting for the investigation to complete.
~~~
put yourself in our shoes - you work your ass off to be a good dad.  you spend all day taking care of your kid(s). you want nothing but the best for your kid and peace and quiet from everyone else.  suddenly, you receive a call from a sex crimes detective stating that you’ve been accused of horrible things (they won’t tell you what the accusations are to protect the “victims”). you’re not allowed to have any contact with your child.  you have no idea how they’re doing.  what they’re being told.  where they are.  you haven’t slept for weeks.  your family is distraught.  you’re facing serious criminal prosecution.
~~~
what would you do?
~~~
#metoo #himtoo #believewomen #falseaccusations #childcustody #whatwouldyoudo #imissmyson #ilovemyboy

text:
#metoo
.
.
i recently experienced the all too common ass slap from someone who i thought i was a trusted yoga instructor (someone who happens to be a 60 year-old white male). this was the second time it happened. the first time i brushed it off as something accidental - maybe it was a playful slap aiming for the leg, but happened to get the wrong spot. this time it was clear that it was not. 
i happened to be going to this class with onyx’s dad, who witnessed it. he was totally horrified and distraught. ready to totally write off the yoga scene, saying that it’s full of predatory men who take advantage of women in tight yoga clothes. while this is unfortunately true in some cases, i let him know that sexual assault and harassment is a societal problem. it exists across the board, and swept under the rug again, and again - #kavanaugh doesn’t even need mentioning here, but it so blatantly displays all that is wrong in this country, and this happened to occur right before that trial. i also let him know that this was not the first time this happened to me in my lifetime, nor the worst scenario, and sadly it likely won’t be the last. 
this event sparked a great conversation between he and i, around this topic, and how we want to raise our daughter in this world - so i see the light in the experience. there were moments after it happened that i found myself unsettled by the yoga scene. i was letting someone take away the healing of this practice. but i decided to say nope. i’m not going to let someone have that power over me. someone who clearly needs more healing than. so i’m focusing on compassion, and modeling the change i wish to see to all the young lives i impact as a mother and teacher. my voice may be one, but i have the power to impact many. the narrative is shifting, and change is coming.
.
.
.
#endpatriarchy #mother #teacher #lover #femininerising #divinefeminine #feminist #yoga #yogacommunity #malasana #spirituality #healing #forgiveness #selflove #motherhoodrising

text_retweet:
having been raped multiple times in my life, i have a lot of experience with forgiveness.
.
i held onto my anger and pain as if they would protect me from further trespasses when in truth, i was held by them and by my wounded memories which had become my greatest perpetrator.
.
i was in purgatory, afraid to live and yet not willing to die to what was.
.
forgiveness came in the piercing moment of this awareness; and in a rush of self-love and courage, i gave back what was never mine & reclaimed everything that was.
🙌🏻💜🙌🏻
*************
this is a repost of an old one of mine. seems like many are asking for this right now. and forgiveness is so much easier when we realize who we are truly setting free.
💘rebecca
.
i am here for you, sisters. let me help you find your moment of forgiveness. one is all it takes. 😉
.
i will be offering private sessions—#traumahealing #shamanichealing and #spiritualmentoring—in #venicebeach 10/26-10/28. i’m even bringing my 🔥 cleansing gear!! 💃
pm me to grab your spot!
.
#forgiveness #heforshe #embracedmasculine #shamelessfeminine #metoo #whyididntreport #thankyoudrford #womensreality #yesallwomen #everdaysexism #shero #traumhealing #traumaheals #shamanichealing #laheals #travelingshaman #shamansister

text:
deep. juicy. vibrant. electric. when women come together, there is a certain magic that is both palpable and inexplicable.

when we step foot on the path of healing and transformation, it becomes essential to surround ourselves with a supportive community of people who can hold space for us to go through our process. given the context of our current #metoo culture, it has never felt so crucial to surround ourselves with soulful sisters as we embark on a journey to reclaim our sexual sovereignty.

it's not always easy to cultivate this kind of relationship with other women in the context of our regular lives. we are conditioned to believe that women are critical, competitive, catty, and even vicious. and after generations of socialized behavior, we often show up that way. 
does this sound familiar to you? it doesn't have to be this way. 
knowing how many women struggle in their relationships with women, i wove into the fabric of my programs the kind of compassion, connection, and intimacy that serves as a foundation for healing and reinventing what's possible inside of sisterhood.

one of the most compelling things you will get from your participation in my upcoming 12-week program, holy sexy you, is the opportunity to be held in the safety of a pod of powerful women who are each on a parallel journey to find their way home to themselves.

i invite you to consider what it might mean for you at this point in your journey to spend some time in the structured company of women doing deep, transformational work. what might that bring to your life at this time?

learn more: link in bio

#sisterhood #transformation #sexuality #holysexyyou #women #spirituality #tantra #metamorphosis #spiritualpath

text:
dear glory baby,

you behold heaven’s light, glory’s morning never fading. and though your loss brings gloom’s shadow, we rejoice in knowing you'll never know true darkness, you'll never know the night.
and i will never feel your warmth, your little form in elbow’s crook. yet my arms lift up hallelujahs to your maker, who has hemmed you into his wings eternal. stitch by glorious stitch. 
our souls rub sore, realizing you are absent from your sister-twin, your kindred half. yet you are honored in her every moment. every breath is a memoir. every laugh a requiem. 
and though you never made your mark, no footprints, nor heartbeat— you are forever impressed upon ours. and ours, my little love, will always beat in hopeful expectation until the moment our eyes meet. 
you are always loved, you are never forgotten.

love, 
your mommy forever

#infantandpregnancylossawarenessday #pregnancyandinfantlossawarenessmonth #youarenotalone #metoo #itiswellwithmysoul #onethousandgifts

text:
$125.00cad

it has been decided! i will call this piece "resiliance". ☉

i decided on this name for a few reasons... 1. i have struggled this year having being let go and non stop job hunting weighing on my self confidence and self worth.
2. there has been a lot of negative news in the world. whether it be ongoing war in the throughout the world, sexual assault/harassment and the #metoo movement, and the ongoing shootings and terrorism that seems to be on constant rerun in the news to name a few. and yet throughout all of this i'm constantly in awe of the resilience that is shown by survivors.
3. with its textured yellow bursting through and rising up against the heavy black makes my heart sing and reminds me of the light stamping out the dark, and the good overcoming the bad. ☉

a great reminder for all of us. no matter how big or how small our struggles are with hard work and resilience we can make a difference and we can rise up.

text:
crying children all day.  small house, tiny kitchen, and the favorite upstairs washroom.  the only part i’ll remember about today was braiden running into the matte box.  no marks.  all good.  little champ;)
pic from yesterday.  i got nothin.
word of the day: patzer
1 - a casual, amateurish chess player.
origin: patzer was first recorded in 1955–60. it is probably from german patzer “bungler”.
history of today: 10/15/18
friedrich nietzsche and tito jackson share this birthday;)
in 1917, the most famous spy of world war i, gertrude zelle, better known as mata hari, was executed by a firing squad outside paris. zelle was an exotic dancer who admitted to giving the germans information but insisted it was only to learn secrets to slip to the french.
i’m just sexy dancing whilst smoking and talking to this french dude!  no big deal guys!
in 1966, huey p. newton and bobby seale founded the black panther party (originally the black panther party for self-defense) with the goal of harnessing anger within the black community and channeling it into a political force.
in 1984, astronomers in pasadena, calif., displayed the first photographic evidence of another solar system 293 trillion miles from earth.
i was 2.  big year.  guys lets put space on hold a decade of two and get things a little more on point down here eh?
in 2017, actor alyssa milano launched the #metoo social media campaign, encouraging victims of sexual assault to break their silence and share their stories in the wake of accusations against harvey weinstein.
soo many dirt bags.
a thought for the day: "always forgive your enemies; nothing annoys them so much." -- oscar wilde

text: "even as we must treat accusers with seriousness and dignity, we must hear out the accused fairly and respectfully, and recognize the potential lifetime consequences that such an allegation can bring," writes emily yoffe in an atlantic article about the fallout from the brett kavanaugh hearings. "if believing the woman is the beginning and the end of a search for the truth, then we have left the realm of justice for religion." we should expect the formal arbiters of justice—police, prosecutors, judges, juries, etc.—to take an even-handed approach to such cases. and we should want the informal arbiters of justice—media, activists, the broader public—to exercise some degree of caution. an activist culture at war with the principles of due process and the broader presumption of innocence is a bigger threat to black convenience-store kids as it is to rich and powerful men. justice for victims must not come at the expense of fairness for the accused."- robby soave #feminism #metoo #fourthwavefeminism

text:
👑لمتابعيناالكرام 👑
⚜ لاهميه الصبار. وفوائد المعروفة على مر السنين. فان شركة فوريفر تحتكر انتاج الصبار على مستوى العالم حيث تمتلك 85‎%‎ من الانتاج العالمي من الصبار 
وافضل مافى الامر ان الشركه تهتم بالامر من البدايه من زراعه النبات وحتى تحويله  الى المنتجات عاليه الجوده💪 اللى نتمتع بيها الان👌

اهمية إستخدام الصبار في أجسامنا لهذه الأشهر الثلاثة؟

الشهر الاول
- تنظيف الجهاز الهضمي كله (الكبد والطحال والبنكرياس والمعدة والأمعاء)
- ينظم المرور العابر وينظف القولون الزوائد
- يزيل السموم
- تطهير الجسم
- يدمر الخلايا الميتة

الشهر الثاني
- إعادة تنشيط جميع وظائف الجسم الأخرى (مثل ما يلعب في النوم، والعصبية، والوزن، ...)
- تحسين وتنشيط جهاز المناعة والدورة الدموية
- يساعد على مكافحة جميع الاعتداءات الحياة الحديثة

الشهر الثالث
- إعادة التوازن في التمثيل الغذائي
- تحسين نوعية تجديد
للتواصل عبر الخاص.  #كلنا_ثقه_في_محمد_بن_سلمان #لازما_العايل_زمينا #السعودية_العظمى #تصريح #metoo #السعودية

text:
the truth is ... i dont need a single day to remember you.. i remember you everyday .. in your twin sister
in your 3 brothers 
in every moment we feel like a complete family i remember you.. in every butterfly, ladybug and rainbow.. in the family of bluejays thats taken up residency in our backyard .. in every family photo at every milestone in and smile in ellen you are always with us .. losing a child while having others is like splitting your heart between heaven and earth everyday of your life.. your presence is always felt and you will be forever missed sweet girl veronica anne until we meet again 💖🙏 love, mommy

#siugr #iugr #twinmomx2 #childloss #twinlesstwin #twinmomchildloss #iugrawareness #siugrawareness #momof5 #heaven #angels #familyof7 #metoo

text:
#newepisode🎧•
•
our latest episode is featuring lawyer, writer, & advocate nicki hamilton, @toomanynix.

nicki shared with us her story, and we were left in awe of her bravery & strength.

nicki was living what she describes as a perfect life up until the age of 14. this was the age when new circumstances meant that nicki no longer had to spend as much time at home as usual. in typical teenage behavior, this is when she began explore life outside of her normal routine. she met new friends, went new places, and found new parts of herself. as most do when presented with new opportunities. unfortunately for nicki, her new found freedom was short lived. she quickly caught the eye of her small town’s most notorious young trouble maker who decided to pursue her relentlessly. in fact, he went on to sexually assault her twice, stalk her at home and at school, send people to track her whereabouts, and slowly control every aspect of nicki’s young life. 
in this interview, nicki describes exactly how, in just a few short weeks, her life changed forever. she shifted into a fearful teenager who was being stalked by her abuser. and because she was afraid of the possibility of accusations and repercussions from her family and the people of her town she internalized the experience and decided that what was happening was her own fault, rape was sex, and that she needed to create an unattractive version of herself in order to survive. so, in turn, she withdrew, became mean, and started to dress in baggy clothes.

later in life, she found therapy and landed her feet on a path towards healing. in this episode, nicki helps us understand the signs of someone who may be silently crying out for help and she provides valuable tips on what to and not to say to a victim. •
•

text:
today i had to do one of the most difficult things i’ve ever had to do in my life...
i said goodbye to my best friend and love of my life, pepe. he came to me during the darkest years of my life. he licked my tears and made me laugh. and most of all he taught me what unconditional love truly is. 
and no coincidence that he planned to leave this particularly day because this is the day i planned to send my book off to print. 📖his assignment was complete. 
it’s very quiet here tonight with internet down due to storms and no movement in my home, but i know he’s in a much better place-still guarding and watching over me. i love you pepe. 🙏❤️

text:
la ex secretaria de estado de ee.uu. hillary clinton dijo hoy 14 de octubre de 2018, que la relación de su esposo, bill clinton, con mónica lewinsky no fue un abuso de poder porque la entonces becaria de la casa blanca tenía 22 años y ya "era un adulto". en un momento de gran debate feminista y de auge del movimiento #metoo, que ella misma ha defendido,fue preguntada en la cadena cbs sobre si su esposo debería haber renunciado a la presidencia después de que el asunto saliera a la luz, a lo que hillary clinton dijo: "absolutamente, no". preguntada de nuevo sobre si bill clinton (1993-2001) habría cometido un abuso de poder, ya que un presidente de los estados unidos no podía tener una relación de consenso con una becaria, agregó: "no, no" porque lewinsky "era un adulto". la conducta sexual de bill clinton abocó en 1998 al entonces presidente a un proceso de destitución, aunque finalmente fue exonerado por el congreso. en marzo pasado, en una columna en la revista vanity fair, lewinsky afirmó que existió cierto "abuso inapropiado de la autoridad" por parte de clinton. "ahora me doy cuenta de lo problemático que fue hasta que los dos llegáramos a la cuestión del consentimiento. el camino que llevaba hasta allí estaba plagado de abuso inapropiado de la autoridad, posición y privilegio", escribió lewinsky.

text: culture and politics today are riven with debates about social justice. #blacklivesmatter and the #metoo movement are social justice campaigns which have become international phenomena. at the heart of these movements are so-called “social justice warriors”: people who take to the streets (and their keyboards and phones) to promote their vision of social justice. but what does it mean to be a social justice warrior, and should we become one? join outreach director james croft oct. 21 at 11 a.m. for his talk on social justice warriors.

text:
🔊 #nothingtoseehere #lovely #ego #winning — #donaldtrump has an unusual portrait hanging in the white house.
-
sharp-eyed viewers of his strange “60 minutes” interview on sunday night noticed a portrait on the wall of trump sitting at a table with other former republican presidents, including abraham lincoln, ronald reagan and richard m. nixon:
-
the portrait is one of a number of presidential images created by #artist andy thomas, who has painted both democrats and republicans. he told time earlier this year that he considers himself an independent who supported both reagan and former president bill clinton.
-
thomas said #trump was “outside the norm,” which made him an interesting subject:
-
“is he going to end up going in history as a great republican or an abnormality or something? so it’s interesting. i just put him at the table, more or less the center of attention. we’ll let history decide. or let the people decide. it’s not up to me.”
-
thomas said trump was a little hard to paint because his light hair, tan skin and lack of dark recesses under his eyes make his face mostly just “a light warm color.” he also found it hard to give trump a “genuine smile,” and had to redo the painting after his first take seemed off.
-
trump later made a “real gracious call” to say how much he liked the portrait.
-
“he was very complimentary,” thomas said. “he made a comment that he’d seen a lot of paintings of himself and he rarely liked them.”
-
thomas said the decision to include a woman was not a commentary on trump or the revelations about sexual misconduct among political and business leaders at the time. instead, he said it grew out of a more artistic decision.
-
that led him to the decision to add a group of people in the background, which led him to decide a woman would approach the table.
-
“i’m an old-fashioned male,” he said. “but there’s a feeling of a good old boy’s network that i wanted to dispel. it just kind of came about.”
-
he does have one inspiration, his daughter jenny. “jenny would do that,” he said. “she’d walk right up there.”
—
#truth #metoo #obama #wereallthesame #historyrepeats #diversity #dumptrump #fucktrump thanks! @liberalblizzard

***

text:
my handmaid's costume arrived today. the hand bell came last week.  now i need to finish the sandwich board and posters i'll be displaying.  just in time for the first day of early voting. 
on voting days i'll be ringing out "shame, shame, shame" as voters head to the building to vote.  i want to remind voters of what's occurred under the current administration. items like: 
health care
separation of children from their parents
banning muslims from entering the us
the #metoo movement
trump's misogynistic actions
foisting christian religious views upon all of america
and on and on and on.

text: tomorrow night i am opening for the fiercely brilliant @yesimsarahjones in support of @takeleadwomen at the creative artists agency in l.a. i am thrilled to be performing poetry before sarah’s powerful show to amplify the vital work of take the lead, a visionary project devoted to helping women step into their power and become catalysts for change. right now, as we are facing such a repressive, misogynistic political environment, i am celebrating the ways we can come together to create art, movements, stories and strategies to take back our power and live our truth. survivors, i see you. survivors, i hear you. survivors, i believe you. be gentle with yourself. take time to replenish. renew your spirit and when you are ready to unleash your wild and worthy voice, let me hear you sing your warrior song. #metoo #sheisrising

i can feel deeply grateful for what i have and ready to create more.
.
love the heck out of my kids while they’re driving me insane.
.
lead powerful conversations while managing my own fear of doing so.
.
check out this episode (before a new one drops tomorrow!) for more on courage, women’s voices, speaking up, and supporting each other.

text:
thanks to @nealthea for bringing this to my attention. @nytgender has been running a campaign called #thisis18, encouraging women to share advice they’d give their 18 year-old selves, along with a photo (feast your eyes upon this gem from my friend’s dorm room - the original #selfie, circa 2004). so, here goes:

break up with your boyfriend before you leave for college. it will make freshman year much easier. don’t be such a jerk to your mom - fast forward 14 years (ackkkkk) and you’ll be spending more time on the phone with her than literally anyone else. you’re beautiful. duke will try to make you think you’re not, but you are. stop pretending to be unintelligent because you think your brainpower is a “turn off” - don’t wait until you’re 25 to figure out that anyone turned off by your smarts isn’t worth your time. enjoy every moment with your friends - even though luckily, the girls you ended high school with are still your close friends over a decade later. stop tanning. you’re pasty - deal with it. your 30 year old skin will thank you. 
and the biggest one of all, the one that’s the most difficult to put down into words: report those men that assaulted you in your dorm room, and tell your story. you did not deserve what happened to you, and you deserve to feel safe and be heard. you are stronger than you think. you will get through this. and they deserve to be held accountable.

#metoo #thisis18 #flashback #retrospective #nytgender #nyt #thefutureisfemale

text:
i’ve decided to pause my #90daydiary with @90_day_depression for a couple of weeks as halloween posts are cropping up more and more as we get closer to the holiday on all social media platforms. these are spurring on memories that have restarted my flashbacks, invasive thoughts, facial twitch and worst of all, sleep paralysis with hallucinations included in each episode. 
i’ll possibly still be looking through and posting my usual but i don’t want to pressure myself to think of something to write or process feelings out loud over the next fortnight at least, as they, i feel, are going to be feelings that i haven’t had to go through yet and may need to fully process on my own or maybe even with a professional.
.

i will return to finish it as i am so invested in this and may take notes on my phone to post when i feel up to it, whether as part of the diary or not.

here’s a sickly sweet photo of @franklingthomas and myself falling to sleep together with him laid on a separate pillow above my head a couple of days ago to keep the cat posts up.

“i have been doubted, hated, talked about, made fun of, hurt, lied to, broken and at my wits end. with that being said, i commend myself for the fact that i am still standing. my courage speaks volume! i know my strength and the pain i’ve endured. i am more than a conqueror. nothing can keep me down and no one can steal my joy. i didn’t give up, i continued to stand tall and love myself first. i am appreciated and unbroken, still i smile”😘

text:
::catharsis:: the chrysalis of your consciousness 
is in it's metamorphosis.

you're dying, 
liquifying. 
so, break... shatter. 
into a thousand tiny pieces.

let the stampedes of story rupture the silence

dissolve the compliance... to witness and consume violence. 
because the assault of the soul happens on all levels

and the system itself will conjure a cause for the rebel

the question is, where do you stand, and what do you stand to gain?

to live out the prophecy of your sovereignty.

you'll never be the same.

so alchemise the pain into medicine and then put yourself back together again.

rearranged

recoded

redefined... cos you could die all your metaphoric deaths and still wake up asleep, 
the bardo is for those who eternally seek.

you have to remember to find the reason to

rise. 
free.

wise.

you see how, now?

when all around purges tricky shadows, black and stark, 
there is always someone who will sit with you in the dark... until you remember that spark that resides,

deep, within your heart.

behind the face and the farce your old persona

the true you shines through

and gifts you a flicker, a shimmer... a glimmer of hope

when worlds collide at the end of a rope,

stand firm on the ground and turn it to a tether,

because this storm, no matter how big, is only weather.

so wash it all away and start a new dreaming

with curiosity you will see your life anchor with deeper meaning

there is as much beauty in the broken, as there is power in the process. 
the majick will be revealed when you start to focus.

artwork: 'autumn metamorphosis' by cynthia sheppard

text:
earlier this year, #donaldtrump was caught in a video that quickly went viral, showing the president refusing to share his umbrella with his wife and 12-year-old son. .
on monday, tv cameras captured trump in a similarly thoughtless moment on the white house lawn. as he and his wife, #melania trump, prepared to board the #marineone helicopter — starting their journey to the florida panhandle where, reuters reports, they arrived later monday — trump was distracted by reporters en route.
.
trump holds an umbrella over himself as he chats with reporters. but when #melaniatrump appears to join him, he makes no move to protect her from the rain with his #umbrella.
.
instead, trump walks several steps towards the tv cameras, leaving melania trump standing by herself in the rain. when he rejoins her, she moves herself under the umbrella, but he continues to make no move to share it with her.
.

text:
i wrote about hillary clinton's statements denying that bill clinton wasn't abusing his power when he started a sexual relationship with an 22-year-old intern. #linkinstories #linkinbio for full piece

i've been doing a lot of reading about trauma and it keeps coming back to the act of compassion. first, it's about building compassion about ourselves (yay #selfcompassion!), but through doing that i found it easier to practice compassion for others, too. it encourages me to think about context and what the other person may be feeling and facing.

what if we did that every time someone says—in good faith—that they've been wronged? what if clinton used an answer based on what monica lewinsky feels about the situation. monica herself said clinton abused his power.  she's a grown woman now, too, no?

in a vanity fair essay, lewinsky wrote: " i now see how problematic it was that the two of us even got to a place where there was a question of consent. instead, the road that led there was littered with inappropriate abuse of authority, station, and privilege. (full stop.)" when it comes to power and consent, what's *legal* isn't what's always *ethical* or *right*—and i believe the onus was on the president to do the right thing and set that boundary. his privilege and power allowed him to feel comfortable to do it—and then lewinsky ends up being publicly bullied as she's used as a political pawn.

the best way to understand harm is to talk to the people who've been harmed. even if it is not intentional there's still value in taking time to sit and consider their point of view, even if it's to make you more sure of your own. i think if we used this approach in every aspect of life, believing survivors will come much more naturally.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#consent #abuse #metoo #monicalewinsky #antibullying #compassion #affirmativeconsent

tw: #metoo #whyididntreport r*pe
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
this was me. two years ago on this date. just hours before a very traumatic event had taken place in my life. i really miss being the person in this photo. 
this person just came back to nyc from a fashion week seeking modeling agency representation in france excursion, was so motivated and dedicated to enhance an ongoing modeling career and upgrade my portfolio, and was determined to make it in nyc and elsewhere. it was until something happened in the early morning hours of saturday morning october 15th, 2016 in bushwick and that changed this person’s life forever. 
well, i am indeed that person and til this day i still struggle with the fact that i was violently sexually assaulted two years ago. i try to push it to the back of mind and pretend like it ‘never happened’ or that it’s such a ‘distant memory’, but tbh the wound and trauma is still there. i feel like ever since that man violated me and went against my “no”, my life deteriorated and went down hill from there. for those who know me well, y’all know these past two years have been extremely rough for me. i don’t have the repeat the bs, but y’all know. i’m dead trying my hardest to be the best person that i can be and to live and move on with my life. with the talks of kavagnag or however you spell his name, cosby, that borns singer, and so many other well known predators in our society, i’ve just been silent and not bother in participating in the #metoo #whyididntreport hashtags, but since today is my traumaversary, i got some shit to say. 
i didn’t report because i was a scared lil ole 20 year old girl with barely any family in ny nor did not have a decent support system at the time. i was afraid nypd wouldn’t believe a god damn word on what i gotta say nor take it seriously. i was also afraid for my safety as well because my rapist is a drug dealer and i was afraid i was gonna catch charges in regards of the illegal under age drinking and coke used that night of the party. i was a young black survival sex worker in nyc and i thought my words wouldn’t matter nor wouldn’t be validated. more is continued in the comments ⬇️

text:
i am disappointed at all the bullshit that i hear of young models being sexually harassed or manipulated in the sacramento community and it is not okay. for those who are being accused please realize you are shooting models for art or for your job not as a sex hook up. to play it safe take every shoot as if it is your paying job to be professional and respectful. it is disappointing to hear some stories from young models dealing with sexual harassment from photographers who are well known in the community. even though some may doubt the victims' credibility, please be aware it also takes great strength and courage for these girls to speak up against their accusers to the public.

i have gone through this multiple times as well at different work places when i even had credible evidence against my harassers. unfortunately in a man's world the companies did not take sufficient action to address my issue which resulted me to either quit my job or continue to work in a hostile work environment for a little longer before i found another job.

thus be the change. for photographers out there please be sensitive and respectful to all the models you shoot with. no women wants to be forced to do something they are not comfortable to do or what you ask them to do. plus keep your hands to yourself. it is not okay to touch a model or flirt with them as it is not professional.

i want to shout out to @vintage_barbiedoll and @rhibogart for being courageous and strong to speak out about this issue and to other beautiful models who directly experienced the harassment from these photographers. plus shout out to the other photographers like @laceymc for speaking out about this issue as well. all of you are inspiring and courageous women. #bethechange #respect #inspire

text:
“this #metoo, this #timesup: this is your pentagon papers moment. so, i think the movie really did meet its moment in time. and the time’s up! so let’s go girls. let’s go, let’s go, let’s go! let’s roll.” - meryl streep, accepting the national board of review's best actress award for her performance in ‘the post’ #leadingwomen ✨⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
'the post' centered around katherine graham, the first female publisher of a major newspaper, and her decision to publish the pentagon papers in the washington post, which was a turning point in us history and president nixon’s presidency. ✨⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
coincidentally, the film was released 8 days before the #timesup movement was formed by women in hollywood as a response to #metoo. thank you to all of the strong women who have raised their hands throughout history and who stand up for what’s right. ✊

text:
monday motivation: "i consider that our present sufferings are not worth comparing with the glory that will be revealed in us." romans 8:18

inspired by a young tenacious me. the me that believed one day the glory would be revealed, if she just held on. 
today, she reminds me that i am... brave. courageous. strong. 
intelligent. resilient. resourceful. 
confident. bold. beautiful. 
loving. loved. beloved. 
witty. talented. bold. 
annointed. appointed. capable.

how could she know what i am? because she reminds me that this is the work she has done. it's our foundation. that she is me. that i am her. and what was in her then, remains in me now. she reminds me...that she did it because of the promise of glory. and that gods promise of glory cannot return to him void! she reminds me there is no comparison...then vs now! that glory is coming.

so, this week i pray you tap into what's at your foundation & gain strenght from the overlooked work you've already done!!! most importantly remember glory is coming. #mondaymotivation #lifestyleblogger #metoo #empower #motivation #live #life #glory #godsgirl #redemption #bible #scripture #inspiration

text:
cet homme m’a écrit une première fois le 4 octobre. puis le 5. puis le 10. puis le 11. je ne réponds pas mais il réitère aujourd’hui. il insiste. fatiguée je lui réponds, il me dit qu’il souhaite simplement "échanger dans l’instant présent". mais les gars vous nous prenez pour des connes à quel point en fait ? et de quel échange on parle quand le dit échange commence avec une insistance vraiment gênante ? je ne vous poste même pas la suite de la conversation dans laquelle il me dit qu’il aime les belles femmes; bien entendu j’ai fini par le bloquer après avoir tenté de lui démontrer sa connerie.

sérieusement je trouve ça dingue d’avoir à le préciser mais puisqu’il le faut je vais le faire encore : je ne suis aucunement ici pour me faire draguer. un compliment authentique, pas déplacé et sans attentes ni arrières-pensées ne me gêne pas, mais ça c’est gênant oui. franchement les gars arrêtez d’écrire aux femmes comme ça, en insistant. je ressens juste l’énergie d’un pervers qui tente de cacher ses intentions dégueulasses derrière un masque faussement gentil. vraiment c’est usant. des messages d’hommes déplacés ou plein d’arrières-pensées j’en reçois quotidiennement (c’est le deuxième aujourd’hui) et je ne réponds quasi jamais (sauf quand vraiment ça me fatigue et ça m’énerve comme aujourd’hui). je pense que je vais commencer à répondre en clashant et je vais afficher ceux qui m’écrivent maintenant. je l’ai dit plein de fois sur tous mes réseaux : je. ne. veux. pas. me. faire. draguer. je ne suis pas là pour ça. ici j’affiche mon travail d’écriture et mon blog et je partage mes idées et ma conscience. c’est tout. et franchement c’est usant et ultra-chiant de ressentir les intentions malsaines de certains à mon égard et à l’égard de tant d’autres femmes d’ailleurs. maîtrisez-vous bordel.

je précise que ce post ne s’adresse pas aux hommes corrects et respectueux, je vous vois déjà venir. ce post s’adresse aux gros lourds pervers insistants et irrespectueux. 
#metoo #balancetonporc #metoomovement #coupdegueule #wtf #wtfiswrongwithyou #jenpeuxplusdetreconsidereecommeuneproieouunboutdeviande #noncestnon #nomeansno

text:
me too.
if all the women who have been sexually harassed or assaulted wrote "me too." as a post, we might give people a sense of the magnitude of the problem.  keep the awareness going.  awareness is the basis for change.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
. . . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
one year ago today.
this.
#metoo
i knew i wanted to say something “publicly” about what had happened a year prior, on saturday, october 15, 2016.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
to honor my experience.
to honor being alive, bruises and scrapes healed.
to honor the courage and strength it took to do all the emotional and psychological and somatic healing work i had done up to that point — all the little moment-by-moment steps, all the big moves, all those actions in between.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i remember being anxious all day, not knowing how to say or what to say about it all.
yet it felt important to say something, anything ...
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
...and just as the clock was nearing midnight, on the 1 year anniversary of being raped by a former friend and work colleague, a “normal guy,” i opened ig and there it was
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#metoo
#metoo
#metoo
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i am so grateful for the #metoomovement to give voice to me and so many others.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it’s not over. it’s never fully over.
our relationship to our experience just changes.
and we can turn our pain into medicine, into advocacy, into action.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i am grateful to be able to do just that.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
in love and solidarity with all survivors —
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i see you.
i hear you.
i believe you.
keep going.
you are loved.
